  nickname: lev
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 433894a244f646848a22a9c7d127b66b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Procedures for the Burnt Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Burnt Offering
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called to Moses from the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and said to him, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 1:3, 5.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. When
        you present an animal as an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you may take it from your herd of cattle or your flock of sheep and goats.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CIf the animal you present as a burnt offering is from the herd,
        it must be a male with no defects. Bring it to the entrance of the Tabernacle
        so you[[COMMENT(0)]] may be accepted by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Or <b>it.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Lay your hand on the animal\u2019s head, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will accept its death in your place to purify you, making you right with
        him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for you.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then slaughter the young bull in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence, and Aaron\u2019s sons, the priests, will present the animal\u2019s
        blood by splattering it against all sides of the altar that stands at the
        entrance to the Tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then skin the animal and cut it into pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Aaron the priest will build a wood fire on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They will arrange the pieces of the offering, including the head
        and fat, on the wood burning on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the internal organs and the legs must first be washed with water.
        Then the priest will burn the entire sacrifice on the altar as a burnt offering.
        It is a special gift, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf the animal you present as a burnt offering is from the flock,
        it may be either a sheep or a goat, but it must be a male with no defects. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Slaughter the animal on the north side of the altar in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence, and Aaron\u2019s sons, the priests, will splatter its blood against
        all sides of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then cut the animal in pieces, and the priests will arrange the pieces
        of the offering, including the head and fat, on the wood burning on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the internal organs and the legs must first be washed with water.
        Then the priest will burn the entire sacrifice on the altar as a burnt offering.
        It is a special gift, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIf you present a bird as a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        choose either a turtledove or a young pigeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The priest will take the bird to the altar, wring off its head, and
        burn it on the altar. But first he must drain its blood against the side
        of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The priest must also remove the crop and the feathers[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and throw them in the ashes on the east side of the altar. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: Or <b>the crop and its contents. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is
          uncertain.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then, grasping the bird by its wings, the priest will tear the bird
        open, but without tearing it apart. Then he will burn it as a burnt offering
        on the wood burning on the altar. It is a special gift, a pleasing aroma
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Procedures for the Grain Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Grain Offering
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhen you present grain as an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the offering must consist of choice flour. You are to pour olive oil on it,
        sprinkle it with frankincense, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and bring it to Aaron\u2019s sons, the priests. The priest will scoop
        out a handful of the flour moistened with oil, together with all the frankincense,
        and burn this representative portion on the altar. It is a special gift,
        a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The rest of the grain offering will then be given to Aaron and his
        sons. This offering will be considered a most holy part of the special gifts
        presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIf your offering is a grain offering baked in an oven, it must
        be made of choice flour, but without any yeast. It may be presented in the
        form of thin cakes mixed with olive oil or wafers spread with olive oil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If your grain offering is cooked on a griddle, it must be made of
        choice flour mixed with olive oil but without any yeast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Break it in pieces and pour olive oil on it; it is a grain offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If your grain offering is prepared in a pan, it must be made of choice
        flour and olive oil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CNo matter how a grain offering for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has been prepared, bring it to the priest, who will present it at the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The priest will take a representative portion of the grain offering
        and burn it on the altar. It is a special gift, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The rest of the grain offering will then be given to Aaron and his
        sons as their food. This offering will be considered a most holy part of
        the special gifts presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CDo not use yeast in preparing any of the grain offerings you
        present to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, because no yeast or honey may
        be burned as a special gift presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You may add yeast and honey to an offering of the first crops of
        your harvest, but these must never be offered on the altar as a pleasing
        aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Season all your grain offerings with salt to remind you of God\u2019s
        eternal covenant. Never forget to add salt to your grain offerings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIf you present a grain offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from the first portion of your harvest, bring fresh grain that is coarsely
        ground and roasted on a fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Put olive oil on this grain offering, and sprinkle it with frankincense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The priest will take a representative portion of the grain moistened
        with oil, together with all the frankincense, and burn it as a special gift
        presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Procedures for the Peace Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Peace Offering
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf you present an animal from the herd as a peace offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, it may be a male or a female, but it
        must have no defects. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Lay your hand on the animal\u2019s head, and slaughter it at the
        entrance of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]] Then Aaron\u2019s sons, the priests,
        will splatter its blood against all sides of the altar. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 3:8, 13.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The priest must present part of this peace offering as a special
        gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This includes all the fat around
        the internal organs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the two kidneys and the fat around them near the loins, and the long
        lobe of the liver. These must be removed with the kidneys, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and Aaron\u2019s sons will burn them on top of the burnt offering
        on the wood burning on the altar. It is a special gift, a pleasing aroma
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf you present an animal from the flock as a peace offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, it may be a male or a female, but it
        must have no defects. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If you present a sheep as your offering, bring it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "lay your hand on its head, and slaughter it in front of the Tabernacle.
        Aaron\u2019s sons will then splatter the sheep\u2019s blood against all sides
        of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The priest must present the fat of this peace offering as a special
        gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This includes the fat of the broad
        tail cut off near the backbone, all the fat around the internal organs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the two kidneys and the fat around them near the loins, and the long
        lobe of the liver. These must be removed with the kidneys, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and the priest will burn them on the altar. It is a special gift
        of food presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf you present a goat as your offering, bring it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "lay your hand on its head, and slaughter it in front of the Tabernacle.
        Aaron\u2019s sons will then splatter the goat\u2019s blood against all sides
        of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The priest must present part of this offering as a special gift to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This includes all the fat around the internal
        organs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the two kidneys and the fat around them near the loins, and the long
        lobe of the liver. These must be removed with the kidneys, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and the priest will burn them on the altar. It is a special gift
        of food, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. All the fat
        belongs to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou must never eat any fat or blood. This is a permanent law
        for you, and it must be observed from generation to generation, wherever
        you live.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Procedures for the Sin Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Sin Offering
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. This
        is how you are to deal with those who sin unintentionally by doing anything
        that violates one of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s commands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CIf the high priest[[COMMENT(0)]] sins, bringing guilt upon
        the entire community, he must give a sin offering for the sin he has committed.
        He must present to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> a young bull with no defects. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the anointed priest; </b>also in 4:5, 16.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He must bring the bull to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the
        entrance of the Tabernacle,[[COMMENT(0)]] lay his hand on the bull\u2019s
        head, and slaughter it before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 4:5, 7, 14, 16, 18.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The high priest will then take some of the bull\u2019s blood into
        the Tabernacle, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'dip his finger in the blood, and sprinkle it seven times before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in front of the inner curtain of the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The priest will then put some of the blood on the horns of the altar
        for fragrant incense that stands in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence inside the Tabernacle. He will pour out the rest of the bull\u2019s
        blood at the base of the altar for burnt offerings at the entrance of the
        Tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the priest must remove all the fat of the bull to be offered
        as a sin offering. This includes all the fat around the internal organs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the two kidneys and the fat around them near the loins, and the long
        lobe of the liver. He must remove these along with the kidneys, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'just as he does with cattle offered as a peace offering, and burn
        them on the altar of burnt offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But he must take whatever is left of the bull\u2014its hide, meat,
        head, legs, internal organs, and dung\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and carry it away to a place outside the camp that is ceremonially
        clean, the place where the ashes are dumped. There, on the ash heap, he will
        burn it on a wood fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf the entire Israelite community sins by violating one of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s commands, but the people don\u2019t
        realize it, they are still guilty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When they become aware of their sin, the people must bring a young
        bull as an offering for their sin and present it before the Tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The elders of the community must then lay their hands on the bull\u2019s
        head and slaughter it before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The high priest will then take some of the bull\u2019s blood into
        the Tabernacle, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'dip his finger in the blood, and sprinkle it seven times before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in front of the inner curtain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He will then put some of the blood on the horns of the altar for
        fragrant incense that stands in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence
        inside the Tabernacle. He will pour out the rest of the blood at the base
        of the altar for burnt offerings at the entrance of the Tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the priest must remove all the animal\u2019s fat and burn it
        on the altar, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'just as he does with the bull offered as a sin offering for the high
        priest. Through this process, the priest will purify the people, making them
        right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]] and they will be
        forgiven. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:20 '
        content: Or <b>will make atonement for the people; </b>similarly in 4:26,
          31, 35.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the priest must take what is left of the bull and carry it outside
        the camp and burn it there, just as is done with the sin offering for the
        high priest. This offering is for the sin of the entire congregation of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf one of Israel\u2019s leaders sins by violating one of the
        commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God but doesn\u2019t realize
        it, he is still guilty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he becomes aware of his sin, he must bring as his offering a
        male goat with no defects. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He must lay his hand on the goat\u2019s head and slaughter it at
        the place where burnt offerings are slaughtered before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        This is an offering for his sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then the priest will dip his finger in the blood of the sin offering
        and put it on the horns of the altar for burnt offerings. He will pour out
        the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he must burn all the goat\u2019s fat on the altar, just as he
        does with the peace offering. Through this process, the priest will purify
        the leader from his sin, making him right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and he will be forgiven.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CIf any of the common people sin by violating one of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        commands, but they don\u2019t realize it, they are still guilty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When they become aware of their sin, they must bring as an offering
        for their sin a female goat with no defects. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They must lay a hand on the head of the sin offering and slaughter
        it at the place where burnt offerings are slaughtered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the priest will dip his finger in the blood and put it on the
        horns of the altar for burnt offerings. He will pour out the rest of the
        blood at the base of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he must remove all the goat\u2019s fat, just as he does with
        the fat of the peace offering. He will burn the fat on the altar, and it
        will be a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Through this
        process, the priest will purify the people, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they will be forgiven.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CIf the people bring a sheep as their sin offering, it must
        be a female with no defects. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They must lay a hand on the head of the sin offering and slaughter
        it at the place where burnt offerings are slaughtered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then the priest will dip his finger in the blood of the sin offering
        and put it on the horns of the altar for burnt offerings. He will pour out
        the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then he must remove all the sheep\u2019s fat, just as he does with
        the fat of a sheep presented as a peace offering. He will burn the fat on
        the altar on top of the special gifts presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Through this process, the priest will purify the people from their sin, making
        them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and they will be forgiven."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sins Requiring a Sin Offering'
      title: Sins Requiring a Sin Offering
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf you are called to testify about something you have seen
        or that you know about, it is sinful to refuse to testify, and you will be
        punished for your sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COr suppose you unknowingly touch something that is ceremonially
        unclean, such as the carcass of an unclean animal. When you realize what
        you have done, you must admit your defilement and your guilt. This is true
        whether it is a wild animal, a domestic animal, or an animal that scurries
        along the ground.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201COr suppose you unknowingly touch something that makes a person
        unclean. When you realize what you have done, you must admit your guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201COr suppose you make a foolish vow of any kind, whether its
        purpose is for good or for bad. When you realize its foolishness, you must
        admit your guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen you become aware of your guilt in any of these ways, you
        must confess your sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then you must bring to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as the penalty
        for your sin a female from the flock, either a sheep or a goat. This is a
        sin offering with which the priest will purify you from your sin, making
        you right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Or <b>will make atonement for you for your sin; </b>similarly in
          5:10, 13, 16, 18.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut if you cannot afford to bring a sheep, you may bring to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> two turtledoves or two young pigeons as the
        penalty for your sin. One of the birds will be for a sin offering, and the
        other for a burnt offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You must bring them to the priest, who will present the first bird
        as the sin offering. He will wring its neck but without severing its head
        from the body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then he will sprinkle some of the blood of the sin offering against
        the sides of the altar, and the rest of the blood will be drained out at
        the base of the altar. This is an offering for sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The priest will then prepare the second bird as a burnt offering,
        following all the procedures that have been prescribed. Through this process
        the priest will purify you from your sin, making you right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you will be forgiven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIf you cannot afford to bring two turtledoves or two young
        pigeons, you may bring two quarts[[COMMENT(0)]] of choice flour for your
        sin offering. Since it is an offering for sin, you must not moisten it with
        olive oil or put any frankincense on it. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1/10 of an ephah </b>[2.2 liters].
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take the flour to the priest, who will scoop out a handful as a representative
        portion. He will burn it on the altar on top of the special gifts presented
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. It is an offering for sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Procedures for the Guilt Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Guilt Offering
      number: 13
      content: "Through this process, the priest will purify those who are guilty
        of any of these sins, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they will be forgiven. The rest of the flour will belong to the priest,
        just as with the grain offering.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf one of you commits a sin by unintentionally defiling the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s sacred property, you must bring a guilt
        offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. The offering must be your own
        ram with no defects, or you may buy one of equal value with silver, as measured
        by the weight of the sanctuary shekel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: Each shekel was about 0.4 ounces or 11 grams in weight.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You must make restitution for the sacred property you have harmed
        by paying for the loss, plus an additional 20 percent. When you give the
        payment to the priest, he will purify you with the ram sacrificed as a guilt
        offering, making you right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and you
        will be forgiven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CSuppose you sin by violating one of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        commands. Even if you are unaware of what you have done, you are guilty and
        will be punished for your sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For a guilt offering, you must bring to the priest your own ram with
        no defects, or you may buy one of equal value. Through this process the priest
        will purify you from your unintentional sin, making you right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you will be forgiven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This is a guilt offering, for you have been guilty of an offense
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sins Requiring a Guilt Offering'
      title: Sins Requiring a Guilt Offering
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: '  Verses 6:1-7 are numbered 5:20-26 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSuppose one of you sins against your associate and is unfaithful
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Suppose you cheat in a deal involving
        a security deposit, or you steal or commit fraud, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'or you find lost property and lie about it, or you lie while swearing
        to tell the truth, or you commit any other such sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you have sinned in any of these ways, you are guilty. You must
        give back whatever you stole, or the money you took by extortion, or the
        security deposit, or the lost property you found, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'or anything obtained by swearing falsely. You must make restitution
        by paying the full price plus an additional 20 percent to the person you
        have harmed. On the same day you must present a guilt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As a guilt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you must
        bring to the priest your own ram with no defects, or you may buy one of equal
        value. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Further Instructions for the Burnt Offering'
      title: Further Instructions for the Burnt Offering
      number: 7
      content: "Through this process, the priest will purify you before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        making you right with him,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> and you will be forgiven
        for any of these sins you have committed.\u201D</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:7 '
        content: 'Or <b>will make atonement for you before the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.</b>  '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: '  Verses 6:8-30 are numbered 6:1-23 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CGive Aaron and his sons the following instructions regarding
        the burnt offering. The burnt offering must be left on top of the altar until
        the next morning, and the fire on the altar must be kept burning all night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the morning, after the priest on duty has put on his official
        linen clothing and linen undergarments, he must clean out the ashes of the
        burnt offering and put them beside the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then he must take off these garments, change back into his regular
        clothes, and carry the ashes outside the camp to a place that is ceremonially
        clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Meanwhile, the fire on the altar must be kept burning; it must never
        go out. Each morning the priest will add fresh wood to the fire and arrange
        the burnt offering on it. He will then burn the fat of the peace offerings
        on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Further Instructions for the Grain Offering'
      title: Further Instructions for the Grain Offering
      number: 13
      content: 'Remember, the fire must be kept burning on the altar at all times.
        It must never go out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThese are the instructions regarding the grain offering. Aaron\u2019s
        sons must present this offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in front
        of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The priest on duty will take from the grain offering a handful of
        the choice flour moistened with olive oil, together with all the frankincense.
        He will burn this representative portion on the altar as a pleasing aroma
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Aaron and his sons may eat the rest of the flour, but it must be
        baked without yeast and eaten in a sacred place within the courtyard of the
        Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 6:26, 30.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Remember, it must never be prepared with yeast. I have given it to
        the priests as their share of the special gifts presented to me. Like the
        sin offering and the guilt offering, it is most holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Procedures for the Ordination Offering'
      title: Procedures for the Ordination Offering
      number: 18
      content: "Any of Aaron\u2019s male descendants may eat from the special gifts
        presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This is their permanent right
        from generation to generation. Anyone or anything that touches these offerings
        will become holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201COn the day Aaron and his sons are anointed, they must present
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the standard grain offering of two quarts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of choice flour, half to be offered in the morning and half to be offered
        in the evening. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1/10 of an ephah </b>[2.2 liters].
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It must be carefully mixed with olive oil and cooked on a griddle.
        Then slice[[COMMENT(0)]] this grain offering and present it as a pleasing
        aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:21 '
        content: The meaning of this Hebrew term is uncertain.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In each generation, the high priest[[COMMENT(0)]] who succeeds Aaron
        must prepare this same offering. It belongs to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and must be burned up completely. This is a permanent law. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the anointed priest.</b>
    - name: '23: Further Instructions for the Sin Offering'
      title: Further Instructions for the Sin Offering
      number: 23
      content: "All such grain offerings of a priest must be burned up entirely.
        None of it may be eaten.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CGive Aaron and his sons the following instructions regarding
        the sin offering. The animal given as an offering for sin is a most holy
        offering, and it must be slaughtered in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence at the place where the burnt offerings are slaughtered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The priest who offers the sacrifice as a sin offering must eat his
        portion in a sacred place within the courtyard of the Tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Anyone or anything that touches the sacrificial meat will become
        holy. If any of the sacrificial blood spatters on a person\u2019s clothing,
        the soiled garment must be washed in a sacred place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'If a clay pot is used to boil the sacrificial meat, it must then
        be broken. If a bronze pot is used, it must be scoured and thoroughly rinsed
        with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Any male from a priest\u2019s family may eat from this offering;
        it is most holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: But the offering for sin may not be eaten if its blood was brought
        into the Tabernacle as an offering for purification[[COMMENT(0)]] in the
        Holy Place. It must be completely burned with fire.
      comments:
      - number: '6:30 '
        content: Or <b>an offering to make atonement.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Further Instructions for the Guilt Offering'
      title: Further Instructions for the Guilt Offering
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThese are the instructions for the guilt offering. It is
        most holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The animal sacrificed as a guilt offering must be slaughtered at
        the place where the burnt offerings are slaughtered, and its blood must be
        splattered against all sides of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The priest will then offer all its fat on the altar, including the
        fat of the broad tail, the fat around the internal organs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the two kidneys and the fat around them near the loins, and the long
        lobe of the liver. These are to be removed with the kidneys, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the priests will burn them on the altar as a special gift presented
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This is the guilt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Any male from a priest\u2019s family may eat the meat. It must be
        eaten in a sacred place, for it is most holy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe same instructions apply to both the guilt offering and
        the sin offering. Both belong to the priest who uses them to purify someone,
        making that person right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:7 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the case of the burnt offering, the priest may keep the hide of
        the sacrificed animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Any grain offering that has been baked in an oven, prepared in a
        pan, or cooked on a griddle belongs to the priest who presents it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Further Instructions for the Peace Offering'
      title: Further Instructions for the Peace Offering
      number: 10
      content: 'All other grain offerings, whether made of dry flour or flour moistened
        with olive oil, are to be shared equally among all the priests, the descendants
        of Aaron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThese are the instructions regarding the different kinds of
        peace offerings that may be presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If you present your peace offering as an expression of thanksgiving,
        the usual animal sacrifice must be accompanied by various kinds of bread
        made without yeast\u2014thin cakes mixed with olive oil, wafers spread with
        oil, and cakes made of choice flour mixed with olive oil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This peace offering of thanksgiving must also be accompanied by loaves
        of bread made with yeast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'One of each kind of bread must be presented as a gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        It will then belong to the priest who splatters the blood of the peace offering
        against the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The meat of the peace offering of thanksgiving must be eaten on the
        same day it is offered. None of it may be saved for the next morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf you bring an offering to fulfill a vow or as a voluntary
        offering, the meat must be eaten on the same day the sacrifice is offered,
        but whatever is left over may be eaten on the second day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Any meat left over until the third day must be completely burned
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If any of the meat from the peace offering is eaten on the third
        day, the person who presented it will not be accepted by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        You will receive no credit for offering it. By then the meat will be contaminated;
        if you eat it, you will be punished for your sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CMeat that touches anything ceremonially unclean may not be
        eaten; it must be completely burned up. The rest of the meat may be eaten,
        but only by people who are ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If you are ceremonially unclean and you eat meat from a peace offering
        that was presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you will be cut off
        from the community. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Forbidden Blood and Fat'
      title: The Forbidden Blood and Fat
      number: 21
      content: "If you touch anything that is unclean (whether it is human defilement
        or an unclean animal or any other unclean, detestable thing) and then eat
        meat from a peace offering presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you will be cut off from the community.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. You
        must never eat fat, whether from cattle, sheep, or goats. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The fat of an animal found dead or torn to pieces by wild animals
        must never be eaten, though it may be used for any other purpose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Anyone who eats fat from an animal presented as a special gift to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be cut off from the community. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'No matter where you live, you must never consume the blood of any
        bird or animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: A Portion for the Priests'
      title: A Portion for the Priests
      number: 27
      content: "Anyone who consumes blood will be cut off from the community.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. When
        you present a peace offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, bring part
        of it as a gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Present it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with your own hands
        as a special gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Bring the fat of the
        animal, together with the breast, and lift up the breast as a special offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the priest will burn the fat on the altar, but the breast will
        belong to Aaron and his descendants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Give the right thigh of your peace offering to the priest as a gift. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The right thigh must always be given to the priest who offers the
        blood and the fat of the peace offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For I have reserved the breast of the special offering and the right
        thigh of the sacred offering for the priests. It is the permanent right of
        Aaron and his descendants to share in the peace offerings brought by the
        people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'This is their rightful share. The special gifts presented to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> have been reserved for Aaron and his descendants
        from the time they were set apart to serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "On the day they were anointed, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded
        the Israelites to give these portions to the priests as their permanent share
        from generation to generation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'These are the instructions for the burnt offering, the grain offering,
        the sin offering, and the guilt offering, as well as the ordination offering
        and the peace offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave these instructions to Moses on
        Mount Sinai when he commanded the Israelites to present their offerings to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the wilderness of Sinai.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ordination of the Priests'
      title: Ordination of the Priests
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBring Aaron and his sons, along with their sacred garments,
        the anointing oil, the bull for the sin offering, the two rams, and the basket
        of bread made without yeast, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and call the entire community of Israel together at the entrance
        of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 8:4, 31, 33, 35.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Moses followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s instructions,
        and the whole community assembled at the Tabernacle entrance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Moses announced to them, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has commanded us to do!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he presented Aaron and his sons and washed them with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He put the official tunic on Aaron and tied the sash around his waist.
        He dressed him in the robe, placed the ephod on him, and attached the ephod
        securely with its decorative sash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Moses placed the chestpiece on Aaron and put the Urim and the
        Thummim inside it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He placed the turban on Aaron\u2019s head and attached the gold medallion\u2014the
        badge of holiness\u2014to the front of the turban, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Moses took the anointing oil and anointed the Tabernacle and
        everything in it, making them holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He sprinkled the oil on the altar seven times, anointing it and all
        its utensils, as well as the washbasin and its stand, making them holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then he poured some of the anointing oil on Aaron\u2019s head, anointing
        him and making him holy for his work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Next Moses presented Aaron\u2019s sons. He clothed them in their
        tunics, tied their sashes around them, and put their special head coverings
        on them, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Moses presented the bull for the sin offering. Aaron and his
        sons laid their hands on the bull\u2019s head, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Moses slaughtered it. Moses took some of the blood, and with
        his finger he put it on the four horns of the altar to purify it. He poured
        out the rest of the blood at the base of the altar. Through this process,
        he made the altar holy by purifying it.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:15 '
        content: Or <b>by making atonement for it; </b>or <b>that offerings for purification
          might be made on it.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Moses took all the fat around the internal organs, the long
        lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat around them, and he burned
        it all on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He took the rest of the bull, including its hide, meat, and dung,
        and burned it on a fire outside the camp, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Moses presented the ram for the burnt offering. Aaron and his
        sons laid their hands on the ram\u2019s head, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and Moses slaughtered it. Then Moses took the ram\u2019s blood and
        splattered it against all sides of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then he cut the ram into pieces, and he burned the head, some of
        its pieces, and the fat on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'After washing the internal organs and the legs with water, Moses
        burned the entire ram on the altar as a burnt offering. It was a pleasing
        aroma, a special gift presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Moses presented the other ram, which was the ram of ordination.
        Aaron and his sons laid their hands on the ram\u2019s head, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and Moses slaughtered it. Then Moses took some of its blood and applied
        it to the lobe of Aaron\u2019s right ear, the thumb of his right hand, and
        the big toe of his right foot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Next Moses presented Aaron\u2019s sons and applied some of the blood
        to the lobes of their right ears, the thumbs of their right hands, and the
        big toes of their right feet. He then splattered the rest of the blood against
        all sides of the altar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Next Moses took the fat, including the fat of the broad tail, the
        fat around the internal organs, the long lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys
        and the fat around them, along with the right thigh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "On top of these he placed a thin cake of bread made without yeast,
        a cake of bread mixed with olive oil, and a wafer spread with olive oil.
        All these were taken from the basket of bread made without yeast that was
        placed in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He put all these in the hands of Aaron and his sons, and he lifted
        these gifts as a special offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Moses then took all the offerings back from them and burned them
        on the altar on top of the burnt offering. This was the ordination offering.
        It was a pleasing aroma, a special gift presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Moses took the breast and lifted it up as a special offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This was Moses\u2019 portion of the ram
        of ordination, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Next Moses took some of the anointing oil and some of the blood that
        was on the altar, and he sprinkled them on Aaron and his garments and on
        his sons and their garments. In this way, he made Aaron and his sons and
        their garments holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron and his sons, \u201CBoil the remaining meat
        of the offerings at the Tabernacle entrance, and eat it there, along with
        the bread that is in the basket of offerings for the ordination, just as
        I commanded when I said, \u2018Aaron and his sons will eat it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Any meat or bread that is left over must then be burned up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'You must not leave the Tabernacle entrance for seven days, for that
        is when the ordination ceremony will be completed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Everything we have done today was commanded by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in order to purify you, making you right with him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:34 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for you.</b>
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Now stay at the entrance of the Tabernacle day and night for seven
        days, and do everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> requires. If you
        fail to do this, you will die, for this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has commanded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: So Aaron and his sons did everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded through Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priests Begin Their Work'
      title: The Priests Begin Their Work
      number: 1
      content: '  After the ordination ceremony, on the eighth day, Moses called
        together Aaron and his sons and the elders of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said to Aaron, \u201CTake a young bull for a sin offering and
        a ram for a burnt offering, both without defects, and present them to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then tell the Israelites, \u2018Take a male goat for a sin offering,
        and take a calf and a lamb, both a year old and without defects, for a burnt
        offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Also take a bull[[COMMENT(0)]] and a ram for a peace offering and
        flour moistened with olive oil for a grain offering. Present all these offerings
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will appear to you today.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:4 '
        content: Or <b>cow; </b>also in 9:18, 19.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the people presented all these things at the entrance of the Tabernacle,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        just as Moses had commanded. Then the whole community came forward and stood
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 9:23.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Moses said, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has commanded you to do so that the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        may appear to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron, \u201CCome to the altar and sacrifice your
        sin offering and your burnt offering to purify yourself and the people. Then
        present the offerings of the people to purify them, making them right with
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]] just as he has commanded.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for them.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Aaron went to the altar and slaughtered the calf as a sin offering
        for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His sons brought him the blood, and he dipped his finger in it and
        put it on the horns of the altar. He poured out the rest of the blood at
        the base of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then he burned on the altar the fat, the kidneys, and the long lobe
        of the liver from the sin offering, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The meat and the hide, however, he burned outside the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next Aaron slaughtered the animal for the burnt offering. His sons
        brought him the blood, and he splattered it against all sides of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they handed him each piece of the burnt offering, including
        the head, and he burned them on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then he washed the internal organs and the legs and burned them on
        the altar along with the rest of the burnt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Next Aaron presented the offerings of the people. He slaughtered
        the people\u2019s goat and presented it as an offering for their sin, just
        as he had first done with the offering for his own sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then he presented the burnt offering and sacrificed it in the prescribed
        way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He also presented the grain offering, burning a handful of the flour
        mixture on the altar, in addition to the regular burnt offering for the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Aaron slaughtered the bull and the ram for the people\u2019s
        peace offering. His sons brought him the blood, and he splattered it against
        all sides of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he took the fat of the bull and the ram\u2014the fat of the
        broad tail and from around the internal organs\u2014along with the kidneys
        and the long lobes of the livers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He placed these fat portions on top of the breasts of these animals
        and burned them on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Aaron then lifted up the breasts and right thighs as a special offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, just as Moses had commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After that, Aaron raised his hands toward the people and blessed
        them. Then, after presenting the sin offering, the burnt offering, and the
        peace offering, he stepped down from the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron went into the Tabernacle, and when they came
        back out, they blessed the people again, and the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        appeared to the whole community. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Fire blazed forth from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence
        and consumed the burnt offering and the fat on the altar. When the people
        saw this, they shouted with joy and fell face down on the ground."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin of Nadab and Abihu'
      title: The Sin of Nadab and Abihu
      number: 1
      content: "  Aaron\u2019s sons Nadab and Abihu put coals of fire in their incense
        burners and sprinkled incense over them. In this way, they disobeyed the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by burning before him the wrong kind of fire,
        different than he had commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So fire blazed forth from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence and burned them up, and they died there before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        meant when he said,\u2018I will display my holinessthrough those who come
        near me.I will display my glorybefore all the people.\u2019\u201DAnd Aaron
        was silent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Moses called for Mishael and Elzaphan, Aaron\u2019s cousins,
        the sons of Aaron\u2019s uncle Uzziel. He said to them, \u201CCome forward
        and carry away the bodies of your relatives from in front of the sanctuary
        to a place outside the camp.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they came forward and picked them up by their garments and carried
        them out of the camp, just as Moses had commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron and his sons Eleazar and Ithamar, \u201CDo
        not show grief by leaving your hair uncombed[[COMMENT(0)]] or by tearing
        your clothes. If you do, you will die, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger will strike the whole community of Israel. However, the rest of the
        Israelites, your relatives, may mourn because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        fiery destruction of Nadab and Abihu. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: Or <b>by uncovering your heads.</b>
    - name: '7: Instructions for Priestly Conduct'
      title: Instructions for Priestly Conduct
      number: 7
      content: "But you must not leave the entrance of the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        or you will die, for you have been anointed with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anointing oil.\u201D So they did as Moses commanded.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 10:9.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou and your descendants must never drink wine or any other
        alcoholic drink before going into the Tabernacle. If you do, you will die.
        This is a permanent law for you, and it must be observed from generation
        to generation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You must distinguish between what is sacred and what is common, between
        what is ceremonially unclean and what is clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And you must teach the Israelites all the decrees that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given them through Moses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron and his remaining sons, Eleazar and Ithamar,
        \u201CTake what is left of the grain offering after a portion has been presented
        as a special gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and eat it beside the
        altar. Make sure it contains no yeast, for it is most holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You must eat it in a sacred place, for it has been given to you and
        your descendants as your portion of the special gifts presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        These are the commands I have been given. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the breast and thigh that were lifted up as a special offering
        may be eaten in any place that is ceremonially clean. These parts have been
        given to you and your descendants as your portion of the peace offerings
        presented by the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "You must lift up the thigh and breast as a special offering to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, along with the fat of the special gifts. These
        parts will belong to you and your descendants as your permanent right, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Moses then asked them what had happened to the goat of the sin offering.
        When he discovered it had been burned up, he became very angry with Eleazar
        and Ithamar, Aaron\u2019s remaining sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CWhy didn\u2019t you eat the sin offering in the sacred area?\u201D
        he demanded. \u201CIt is a holy offering! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given it to you to remove the guilt of the community and to purify the
        people, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: '10:17 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for the people before the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Since the animal\u2019s blood was not brought into the Holy Place,
        you should have eaten the meat in the sacred area as I ordered you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Aaron answered Moses, \u201CToday my sons presented both their
        sin offering and their burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And yet this tragedy has happened to me. If I had eaten the people\u2019s
        sin offering on such a tragic day as this, would the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        have been pleased?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And when Moses heard this, he was satisfied.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ceremonially Clean and Unclean Animals'
      title: Ceremonially Clean and Unclean Animals
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\u201COf
        all the land animals, these are the ones you may use for food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You may eat any animal that has completely split hooves and chews
        the cud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You may not, however, eat the following animals[[COMMENT(0)]] that
        have split hooves or that chew the cud, but not both. The camel chews the
        cud but does not have split hooves, so it is ceremonially unclean for you. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: The identification of some of the animals, birds, and insects in
          this chapter is uncertain.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The hyrax[[COMMENT(0)]] chews the cud but does not have split hooves,
        so it is unclean. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:5 '
        content: Or <b>coney, </b>or <b>rock badger.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The hare chews the cud but does not have split hooves, so it is unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The pig has evenly split hooves but does not chew the cud, so it
        is unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You may not eat the meat of these animals or even touch their carcasses.
        They are ceremonially unclean for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201COf all the marine animals, these are ones you may use for food.
        You may eat anything from the water if it has both fins and scales, whether
        taken from salt water or from streams. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But you must never eat animals from the sea or from rivers that do
        not have both fins and scales. They are detestable to you. This applies both
        to little creatures that live in shallow water and to all creatures that
        live in deep water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They will always be detestable to you. You must never eat their meat
        or even touch their dead bodies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Any marine animal that does not have both fins and scales is detestable
        to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThese are the birds that are detestable to you. You must never
        eat them: the griffon vulture, the bearded vulture, the black vulture, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the kite, falcons of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'ravens of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the eagle owl, the short-eared owl, the seagull, hawks of all kinds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the little owl, the cormorant, the great owl, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the barn owl, the desert owl, the Egyptian vulture, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the stork, herons of all kinds, the hoopoe, and the bat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou must not eat winged insects that walk along the ground;
        they are detestable to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You may, however, eat winged insects that walk along the ground and
        have jointed legs so they can jump. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The insects you are permitted to eat include all kinds of locusts,
        bald locusts, crickets, and grasshoppers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'All other winged insects that walk along the ground are detestable
        to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThe following creatures will make you ceremonially unclean.
        If any of you touch their carcasses, you will be defiled until evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'If you pick up their carcasses, you must wash your clothes, and you
        will remain defiled until evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAny animal that has split hooves that are not evenly divided
        or that does not chew the cud is unclean for you. If you touch the carcass
        of such an animal, you will be defiled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Of the animals that walk on all fours, those that have paws are unclean.
        If you touch the carcass of such an animal, you will be defiled until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'If you pick up its carcass, you must wash your clothes, and you will
        remain defiled until evening. These animals are unclean for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201COf the small animals that scurry along the ground, these are
        unclean for you: the mole rat, the rat, large lizards of all kinds, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'the gecko, the monitor lizard, the common lizard, the sand lizard,
        and the chameleon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'All these small animals are unclean for you. If any of you touch
        the dead body of such an animal, you will be defiled until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If such an animal dies and falls on something, that object will be
        unclean. This is true whether the object is made of wood, cloth, leather,
        or burlap. Whatever its use, you must dip it in water, and it will remain
        defiled until evening. After that, it will be ceremonially clean and may
        be used again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CIf such an animal falls into a clay pot, everything in the
        pot will be defiled, and the pot must be smashed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'If the water from such a container spills on any food, the food will
        be defiled. And any beverage in such a container will be defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Any object on which the carcass of such an animal falls will be defiled.
        If it is an oven or hearth, it must be destroyed, for it is defiled, and
        you must treat it accordingly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CHowever, if the carcass of such an animal falls into a spring
        or a cistern, the water will still be clean. But anyone who touches the carcass
        will be defiled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'If the carcass falls on seed grain to be planted in the field, the
        seed will still be considered clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But if the seed is wet when the carcass falls on it, the seed will
        be defiled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CIf an animal you are permitted to eat dies and you touch its
        carcass, you will be defiled until evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'If you eat any of its meat or carry away its carcass, you must wash
        your clothes, and you will remain defiled until evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CAll small animals that scurry along the ground are detestable,
        and you must never eat them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'This includes all animals that slither along on their bellies, as
        well as those with four legs and those with many feet. All such animals that
        scurry along the ground are detestable, and you must never eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Do not defile yourselves by touching them. You must not make yourselves
        ceremonially unclean because of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. You must consecrate
        yourselves and be holy, because I am holy. So do not defile yourselves with
        any of these small animals that scurry along the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'For I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am the one who brought you
        up from the land of Egypt, that I might be your God. Therefore, you must
        be holy because I am holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CThese are the instructions regarding land animals, birds, marine
        creatures, and animals that scurry along the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "By these instructions you will know what is unclean and clean, and
        which animals may be eaten and which may not be eaten.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Purification after Childbirth'
      title: Purification after Childbirth
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. If
        a woman becomes pregnant and gives birth to a son, she will be ceremonially
        unclean for seven days, just as she is unclean during her menstrual period. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "On the eighth day the boy\u2019s foreskin must be circumcised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'After waiting thirty-three days, she will be purified from the bleeding
        of childbirth. During this time of purification, she must not touch anything
        that is set apart as holy. And she must not enter the sanctuary until her
        time of purification is over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If a woman gives birth to a daughter, she will be ceremonially unclean
        for two weeks, just as she is unclean during her menstrual period. After
        waiting sixty-six days, she will be purified from the bleeding of childbirth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CWhen the time of purification is completed for either a son
        or a daughter, the woman must bring a one-year-old lamb for a burnt offering
        and a young pigeon or turtledove for a purification offering. She must bring
        her offerings to the priest at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The priest will then present them to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to purify her.[[COMMENT(0)]] Then she will be ceremonially clean again after
        her bleeding at childbirth. These are the instructions for a woman after
        the birth of a son or a daughter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:7 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for her; </b>also in 12:8.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf a woman cannot afford to bring a lamb, she must bring two
        turtledoves or two young pigeons. One will be for the burnt offering and
        the other for the purification offering. The priest will sacrifice them to
        purify her, and she will be ceremonially clean.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Serious Skin Diseases'
      title: Serious Skin Diseases
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf anyone has a swelling or a rash or discolored skin that
        might develop into a serious skin disease,[[COMMENT(0)]] that person must
        be brought to Aaron the priest or to one of his sons.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:2a '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy. </b>The Hebrew word used throughout
          this passage is used to describe various skin diseases.
      - number: '13:2b '
        content: Or <b>one of his descendants.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The priest will examine the affected area of the skin. If the hair
        in the affected area has turned white and the problem appears to be more
        than skin-deep, it is a serious skin disease, and the priest who examines
        it must pronounce the person ceremonially unclean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBut if the affected area of the skin is only a white discoloration
        and does not appear to be more than skin-deep, and if the hair on the spot
        has not turned white, the priest will quarantine the person for seven days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the seventh day the priest will make another examination. If he
        finds the affected area has not changed and the problem has not spread on
        the skin, the priest will quarantine the person for seven more days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "On the seventh day the priest will make another examination. If he
        finds the affected area has faded and has not spread, the priest will pronounce
        the person ceremonially clean. It was only a rash. The person\u2019s clothing
        must be washed, and the person will be ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But if the rash continues to spread after the person has been examined
        by the priest and has been pronounced clean, the infected person must return
        to be examined again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If the priest finds that the rash has spread, he must pronounce the
        person ceremonially unclean, for it is indeed a skin disease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnyone who develops a serious skin disease must go to the priest
        for an examination. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If the priest finds a white swelling on the skin, and some hair on
        the spot has turned white, and there is an open sore in the affected area, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'it is a chronic skin disease, and the priest must pronounce the person
        ceremonially unclean. In such cases the person need not be quarantined, for
        it is obvious that the skin is defiled by the disease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CNow suppose the disease has spread all over the person\u2019s
        skin, covering the body from head to foot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When the priest examines the infected person and finds that the disease
        covers the entire body, he will pronounce the person ceremonially clean.
        Since the skin has turned completely white, the person is clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But if any open sores appear, the infected person will be pronounced
        ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The priest must make this pronouncement as soon as he sees an open
        sore, since open sores indicate the presence of a skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'However, if the open sores heal and turn white like the rest of the
        skin, the person must return to the priest '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "for another examination. If the affected areas have indeed turned
        white, the priest will then pronounce the person ceremonially clean by declaring,
        \u2018You are clean!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf anyone has a boil on the skin that has started to heal, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'but a white swelling or a reddish white spot develops in its place,
        that person must go to the priest to be examined. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'If the priest examines it and finds it to be more than skin-deep,
        and if the hair in the affected area has turned white, the priest must pronounce
        the person ceremonially unclean. The boil has become a serious skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if the priest finds no white hair on the affected area and the
        problem appears to be no more than skin-deep and has faded, the priest must
        quarantine the person for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'If during that time the affected area spreads on the skin, the priest
        must pronounce the person ceremonially unclean, because it is a serious disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But if the area grows no larger and does not spread, it is merely
        the scar from the boil, and the priest will pronounce the person ceremonially
        clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CIf anyone has suffered a burn on the skin and the burned area
        changes color, becoming either reddish white or shiny white, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'the priest must examine it. If he finds that the hair in the affected
        area has turned white and the problem appears to be more than skin-deep,
        a skin disease has broken out in the burn. The priest must then pronounce
        the person ceremonially unclean, for it is clearly a serious skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But if the priest finds no white hair on the affected area and the
        problem appears to be no more than skin-deep and has faded, the priest must
        quarantine the infected person for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'On the seventh day the priest must examine the person again. If the
        affected area has spread on the skin, the priest must pronounce that person
        ceremonially unclean, for it is clearly a serious skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But if the affected area has not changed or spread on the skin and
        has faded, it is simply a swelling from the burn. The priest will then pronounce
        the person ceremonially clean, for it is only the scar from the burn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CIf anyone, either a man or woman, has a sore on the head or
        chin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'the priest must examine it. If he finds it is more than skin-deep
        and has fine yellow hair on it, the priest must pronounce the person ceremonially
        unclean. It is a scabby sore of the head or chin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'If the priest examines the scabby sore and finds that it is only
        skin-deep but there is no black hair on it, he must quarantine the person
        for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'On the seventh day the priest must examine the sore again. If he
        finds that the scabby sore has not spread, and there is no yellow hair on
        it, and it appears to be only skin-deep, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'the person must shave off all hair except the hair on the affected
        area. Then the priest must quarantine the person for another seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "On the seventh day he will examine the sore again. If it has not
        spread and appears to be no more than skin-deep, the priest will pronounce
        the person ceremonially clean. The person\u2019s clothing must be washed,
        and the person will be ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But if the scabby sore begins to spread after the person is pronounced
        clean, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'the priest must do another examination. If he finds that the sore
        has spread, the priest does not need to look for yellow hair. The infected
        person is ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But if the color of the scabby sore does not change and black hair
        has grown on it, it has healed. The priest will then pronounce the person
        ceremonially clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CIf anyone, either a man or woman, has shiny white patches on
        the skin, "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'the priest must examine the affected area. If he finds that the shiny
        patches are only pale white, this is a harmless skin rash, and the person
        is ceremonially clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CIf a man loses his hair and his head becomes bald, he is still
        ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And if he loses hair on his forehead, he simply has a bald forehead;
        he is still clean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'However, if a reddish white sore appears on the bald area on top
        of his head or on his forehead, this is a skin disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "The priest must examine him, and if he finds swelling around the
        reddish white sore anywhere on the man\u2019s head and it looks like a skin
        disease, "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'the man is indeed infected with a skin disease and is unclean. The
        priest must pronounce him ceremonially unclean because of the sore on his
        head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CThose who suffer from a serious skin disease must tear their
        clothing and leave their hair uncombed.[[COMMENT(0)]] They must cover their
        mouth and call out, \u2018Unclean! Unclean!\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '13:45 '
        content: Or <b>and uncover their heads.</b>
    - name: '46: Treatment of Contaminated Clothing'
      title: Treatment of Contaminated Clothing
      number: 46
      content: 'As long as the serious disease lasts, they will be ceremonially unclean.
        They must live in isolation in their place outside the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CNow suppose mildew[[COMMENT(0)]] contaminates some woolen or
        linen clothing, "
      comments:
      - number: '13:47 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy. </b>The Hebrew term used throughout
          this passage is the same term used for the various skin diseases described
          in 13:1-46.
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'woolen or linen fabric, the hide of an animal, or anything made of
        leather. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'If the contaminated area in the clothing, the animal hide, the fabric,
        or the leather article has turned greenish or reddish, it is contaminated
        with mildew and must be shown to the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'After examining the affected spot, the priest will put the article
        in quarantine for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'On the seventh day the priest must inspect it again. If the contaminated
        area has spread, the clothing or fabric or leather is clearly contaminated
        by a serious mildew and is ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "The priest must burn the item\u2014the clothing, the woolen or linen
        fabric, or piece of leather\u2014for it has been contaminated by a serious
        mildew. It must be completely destroyed by fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "\u201CBut if the priest examines it and finds that the contaminated
        area has not spread in the clothing, the fabric, or the leather, "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'the priest will order the object to be washed and then quarantined
        for seven more days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Then the priest must examine the object again. If he finds that the
        contaminated area has not changed color after being washed, even if it did
        not spread, the object is defiled. It must be completely burned up, whether
        the contaminated spot[[COMMENT(0)]] is on the inside or outside. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:55 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'But if the priest examines it and finds that the contaminated area
        has faded after being washed, he must cut the spot from the clothing, the
        fabric, or the leather. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'If the spot later reappears on the clothing, the fabric, or the leather
        article, the mildew is clearly spreading, and the contaminated object must
        be burned up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'But if the spot disappears from the clothing, the fabric, or the
        leather article after it has been washed, it must be washed again; then it
        will be ceremonially clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "\u201CThese are the instructions for dealing with mildew that contaminates
        woolen or linen clothing or fabric or anything made of leather. This is how
        the priest will determine whether these items are ceremonially clean or unclean.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cleansing from Skin Diseases'
      title: Cleansing from Skin Diseases
      number: 1
      content: '  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe following instructions are for those seeking ceremonial
        purification from a skin disease.[[COMMENT(0)]] Those who have been healed
        must be brought to the priest, "
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy; </b>see note on 13:2a.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'who will examine them at a place outside the camp. If the priest
        finds that someone has been healed of a serious skin disease, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'he will perform a purification ceremony, using two live birds that
        are ceremonially clean, a stick of cedar,[[COMMENT(0)]] some scarlet yarn,
        and a hyssop branch. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:4 '
        content: Or <b>juniper; </b>also in 14:6, 49, 51.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The priest will order that one bird be slaughtered over a clay pot
        filled with fresh water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He will take the live bird, the cedar stick, the scarlet yarn, and
        the hyssop branch, and dip them into the blood of the bird that was slaughtered
        over the fresh water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The priest will then sprinkle the blood of the dead bird seven times
        on the person being purified of the skin disease. When the priest has purified
        the person, he will release the live bird in the open field to fly away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CThe persons being purified must then wash their clothes, shave
        off all their hair, and bathe themselves in water. Then they will be ceremonially
        clean and may return to the camp. However, they must remain outside their
        tents for seven days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'On the seventh day they must again shave all the hair from their
        heads, including the hair of the beard and eyebrows. They must also wash
        their clothes and bathe themselves in water. Then they will be ceremonially
        clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201COn the eighth day each person being purified must bring two
        male lambs and a one-year-old female lamb, all with no defects, along with
        a grain offering of six quarts[[COMMENT(0)]] of choice flour moistened with
        olive oil, and a cup[[COMMENT(1)]] of olive oil. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:10a '
        content: Hebrew <b>3/10 of an ephah </b>[6.6 liters].
      - number: '14:10b '
        content: Hebrew <b>1 log </b>[0.3 liters]; also in 14:21.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the officiating priest will present that person for purification,
        along with the offerings, before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the entrance
        of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 14:23.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The priest will take one of the male lambs and the olive oil and
        present them as a guilt offering, lifting them up as a special offering before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will then slaughter the male lamb in the sacred area where sin
        offerings and burnt offerings are slaughtered. As with the sin offering,
        the guilt offering belongs to the priest. It is a most holy offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The priest will then take some of the blood of the guilt offering
        and apply it to the lobe of the right ear, the thumb of the right hand, and
        the big toe of the right foot of the person being purified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThen the priest will pour some of the olive oil into the palm
        of his own left hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will dip his right finger into the oil in his palm and sprinkle
        some of it with his finger seven times before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The priest will then apply some of the oil in his palm over the blood
        from the guilt offering that is on the lobe of the right ear, the thumb of
        the right hand, and the big toe of the right foot of the person being purified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The priest will apply the oil remaining in his hand to the head of
        the person being purified. Through this process, the priest will purify[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the person before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:18 '
        content: Or <b>will make atonement for; </b>similarly in 14:19, 20, 21, 29,
          31, 53.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen the priest must present the sin offering to purify the
        person who was cured of the skin disease. After that, the priest will slaughter
        the burnt offering "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and offer it on the altar along with the grain offering. Through
        this process, the priest will purify the person who was healed, and the person
        will be ceremonially clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CBut anyone who is too poor and cannot afford these offerings
        may bring one male lamb for a guilt offering, to be lifted up as a special
        offering for purification. The person must also bring two quarts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of choice flour moistened with olive oil for the grain offering and a cup
        of olive oil. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1/10 of an ephah </b>[2.2 liters].
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The offering must also include two turtledoves or two young pigeons,
        whichever the person can afford. One of the pair must be used for the sin
        offering and the other for a burnt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "On the eighth day of the purification ceremony, the person being
        purified must bring the offerings to the priest in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence at the entrance of the Tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The priest will take the lamb for the guilt offering, along with
        the olive oil, and lift them up as a special offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then the priest will slaughter the lamb for the guilt offering. He
        will take some of its blood and apply it to the lobe of the right ear, the
        thumb of the right hand, and the big toe of the right foot of the person
        being purified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe priest will also pour some of the olive oil into the palm
        of his own left hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He will dip his right finger into the oil in his palm and sprinkle
        some of it seven times before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The priest will then apply some of the oil in his palm over the blood
        from the guilt offering that is on the lobe of the right ear, the thumb of
        the right hand, and the big toe of the right foot of the person being purified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The priest will apply the oil remaining in his hand to the head of
        the person being purified. Through this process, the priest will purify the
        person before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThen the priest will offer the two turtledoves or the two young
        pigeons, whichever the person can afford. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'One of them is for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering,
        to be presented along with the grain offering. Through this process, the
        priest will purify the person before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Treatment of Contaminated Houses'
      title: Treatment of Contaminated Houses
      number: 32
      content: "These are the instructions for purification for those who have recovered
        from a serious skin disease but who cannot afford to bring the offerings
        normally required for the ceremony of purification.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CWhen you arrive in Canaan, the land I am giving you as your
        own possession, I may contaminate some of the houses in your land with mildew.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:34 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy; </b>see note on 13:47.
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The owner of such a house must then go to the priest and say, \u2018It
        appears that my house has some kind of mildew.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Before the priest goes in to inspect the house, he must have the
        house emptied so nothing inside will be pronounced ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then the priest will go in and examine the mildew on the walls. If
        he finds greenish or reddish streaks and the contamination appears to go
        deeper than the wall\u2019s surface, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'the priest will step outside the door and put the house in quarantine
        for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'On the seventh day the priest must return for another inspection.
        If he finds that the mildew on the walls of the house has spread, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'the priest must order that the stones from those areas be removed.
        The contaminated material will then be taken outside the town to an area
        designated as ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Next the inside walls of the entire house must be scraped thoroughly
        and the scrapings dumped in the unclean place outside the town. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Other stones will be brought in to replace the ones that were removed,
        and the walls will be replastered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "\u201CBut if the mildew reappears after all the stones have been
        replaced and the house has been scraped and replastered, "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'the priest must return and inspect the house again. If he finds that
        the mildew has spread, the walls are clearly contaminated with a serious
        mildew, and the house is defiled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'It must be torn down, and all its stones, timbers, and plaster must
        be carried out of town to the place designated as ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Those who enter the house during the period of quarantine will be
        ceremonially unclean until evening, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'and all who sleep or eat in the house must wash their clothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CBut if the priest returns for his inspection and finds that
        the mildew has not reappeared in the house after the fresh plastering, he
        will pronounce it clean because the mildew is clearly gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'To purify the house the priest must take two birds, a stick of cedar,
        some scarlet yarn, and a hyssop branch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'He will slaughter one of the birds over a clay pot filled with fresh
        water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'He will take the cedar stick, the hyssop branch, the scarlet yarn,
        and the live bird, and dip them into the blood of the slaughtered bird and
        into the fresh water. Then he will sprinkle the house seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'When the priest has purified the house in exactly this way, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'he will release the live bird in the open fields outside the town.
        Through this process, the priest will purify the house, and it will be ceremonially
        clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "\u201CThese are the instructions for dealing with serious skin diseases,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        including scabby sores; "
      comments:
      - number: '14:54 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy; </b>see note on 13:2a.
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'and mildew,[[COMMENT(0)]] whether on clothing or in a house; '
      comments:
      - number: '14:55 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy; </b>see note on 13:47.
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'and a swelling on the skin, a rash, or discolored skin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "This procedure will determine whether a person or object is ceremonially
        clean or unclean.\u201CThese are the instructions regarding skin diseases
        and mildew.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Bodily Discharges'
      title: Bodily Discharges
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel.\u201CAny
        man who has a bodily discharge is ceremonially unclean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This defilement is caused by his discharge, whether the discharge
        continues or stops. In either case the man is unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Any bed on which the man with the discharge lies and anything on
        which he sits will be ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So if you touch the man\u2019s bed, you must wash your clothes and
        bathe yourself in water, and you will remain unclean until evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If you sit where the man with the discharge has sat, you must wash
        your clothes and bathe yourself in water, and you will remain unclean until
        evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If you touch the man with the discharge, you must wash your clothes
        and bathe yourself in water, and you will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If the man spits on you, you must wash your clothes and bathe yourself
        in water, and you will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Any saddle blanket on which the man rides will be ceremonially unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If you touch anything that was under the man, you will be unclean
        until evening. You must wash your clothes and bathe yourself in water, and
        you will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'If the man touches you without first rinsing his hands, you must
        wash your clothes and bathe yourself in water, and you will remain unclean
        until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Any clay pot the man touches must be broken, and any wooden utensil
        he touches must be rinsed with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWhen the man with the discharge is healed, he must count off
        seven days for the period of purification. Then he must wash his clothes
        and bathe himself in fresh water, and he will be ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On the eighth day he must get two turtledoves or two young pigeons
        and come before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the entrance of the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and give his offerings to the priest. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 15:29.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The priest will offer one bird for a sin offering and the other for
        a burnt offering. Through this process, the priest will purify[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the man before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his discharge.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:15 '
        content: Or <b>will make atonement for; </b>also in 15:30.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWhenever a man has an emission of semen, he must bathe his
        entire body in water, and he will remain ceremonially unclean until the next
        evening.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>until evening; </b>also in 15:18.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Any clothing or leather with semen on it must be washed in water,
        and it will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After a man and a woman have sexual intercourse, they must each bathe
        in water, and they will remain unclean until the next evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhenever a woman has her menstrual period, she will be ceremonially
        unclean for seven days. Anyone who touches her during that time will be unclean
        until evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Anything on which the woman lies or sits during the time of her period
        will be unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If any of you touch her bed, you must wash your clothes and bathe
        yourself in water, and you will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'If you touch any object she has sat on, you must wash your clothes
        and bathe yourself in water, and you will remain unclean until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'This includes her bed or any other object she has sat on; you will
        be unclean until evening if you touch it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If a man has sexual intercourse with her and her blood touches him,
        her menstrual impurity will be transmitted to him. He will remain unclean
        for seven days, and any bed on which he lies will be unclean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CIf a woman has a flow of blood for many days that is unrelated
        to her menstrual period, or if the blood continues beyond the normal period,
        she is ceremonially unclean. As during her menstrual period, the woman will
        be unclean as long as the discharge continues. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Any bed she lies on and any object she sits on during that time will
        be unclean, just as during her normal menstrual period. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'If any of you touch these things, you will be ceremonially unclean.
        You must wash your clothes and bathe yourself in water, and you will remain
        unclean until evening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CWhen the woman\u2019s bleeding stops, she must count off seven
        days. Then she will be ceremonially clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'On the eighth day she must bring two turtledoves or two young pigeons
        and present them to the priest at the entrance of the Tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The priest will offer one for a sin offering and the other for a
        burnt offering. Through this process, the priest will purify her before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for the ceremonial impurity caused by her bleeding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CThis is how you will guard the people of Israel from ceremonial
        uncleanness. Otherwise they would die, for their impurity would defile my
        Tabernacle that stands among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "These are the instructions for dealing with anyone who has a bodily
        discharge\u2014a man who is unclean because of an emission of semen "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "or a woman during her menstrual period. It applies to any man or
        woman who has a bodily discharge, and to a man who has sexual intercourse
        with a woman who is ceremonially unclean.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Day of Atonement'
      title: The Day of Atonement
      number: 1
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Moses after the death
        of Aaron\u2019s two sons, who died after they entered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presence and burned the wrong kind of fire before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CWarn your brother,
        Aaron, not to enter the Most Holy Place behind the inner curtain whenever
        he chooses; if he does, he will die. For the Ark\u2019s cover\u2014the place
        of atonement\u2014is there, and I myself am present in the cloud above the
        atonement cover.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CWhen Aaron enters the sanctuary area, he must follow these
        instructions fully. He must bring a young bull for a sin offering and a ram
        for a burnt offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He must put on his linen tunic and the linen undergarments worn next
        to his body. He must tie the linen sash around his waist and put the linen
        turban on his head. These are sacred garments, so he must bathe himself in
        water before he puts them on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Aaron must take from the community of Israel two male goats for a
        sin offering and a ram for a burnt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAaron will present his own bull as a sin offering to purify
        himself and his family, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:6 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for himself and his family; </b>similarly
          in 16:11, 17b, 24, 34.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then he must take the two male goats and present them to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 16:16, 17, 20, 23, 33.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He is to cast sacred lots to determine which goat will be reserved
        as an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and which will carry the
        sins of the people to the wilderness of Azazel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Aaron will then present as a sin offering the goat chosen by lot
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The other goat, the scapegoat chosen by lot to be sent away, will
        be kept alive, standing before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. When it is
        sent away to Azazel in the wilderness, the people will be purified and made
        right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:10 '
        content: Or <b>wilderness, it will make atonement for the people.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAaron will present his own bull as a sin offering to purify
        himself and his family, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        After he has slaughtered the bull as a sin offering, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'he will fill an incense burner with burning coals from the altar
        that stands before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Then he will take two
        handfuls of fragrant powdered incense and will carry the burner and the incense
        behind the inner curtain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "There in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence he will
        put the incense on the burning coals so that a cloud of incense will rise
        over the Ark\u2019s cover\u2014the place of atonement\u2014that rests on
        the Ark of the Covenant.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> If he follows these instructions,
        he will not die. </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: '16:13 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>that is above the Testimony. </b>The Hebrew word for
          \u201Ctestimony\u201D refers to the terms of the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u2019s
          covenant with Israel as written on stone tablets, which were kept in the
          Ark, and also to the covenant itself."
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then he must take some of the blood of the bull, dip his finger in
        it, and sprinkle it on the east side of the atonement cover. He must sprinkle
        blood seven times with his finger in front of the atonement cover.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThen Aaron must slaughter the first goat as a sin offering
        for the people and carry its blood behind the inner curtain. There he will
        sprinkle the goat\u2019s blood over the atonement cover and in front of it,
        just as he did with the bull\u2019s blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Through this process, he will purify[[COMMENT(0)]] the Most Holy
        Place, and he will do the same for the entire Tabernacle, because of the
        defiling sin and rebellion of the Israelites. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:16 '
        content: Or <b>make atonement for; </b>similarly in 16:17a, 18, 20, 27, 33.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'No one else is allowed inside the Tabernacle when Aaron enters it
        for the purification ceremony in the Most Holy Place. No one may enter until
        he comes out again after purifying himself, his family, and all the congregation
        of Israel, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThen Aaron will come out to purify the altar that stands before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. He will do this by taking some of the blood
        from the bull and the goat and putting it on each of the horns of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he must sprinkle the blood with his finger seven times over
        the altar. In this way, he will cleanse it from Israel\u2019s defilement
        and make it holy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CWhen Aaron has finished purifying the Most Holy Place and the
        Tabernacle and the altar, he must present the live goat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He will lay both of his hands on the goat\u2019s head and confess
        over it all the wickedness, rebellion, and sins of the people of Israel.
        In this way, he will transfer the people\u2019s sins to the head of the goat.
        Then a man specially chosen for the task will drive the goat into the wilderness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As the goat goes into the wilderness, it will carry all the people\u2019s
        sins upon itself into a desolate land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWhen Aaron goes back into the Tabernacle, he must take off
        the linen garments he was wearing when he entered the Most Holy Place, and
        he must leave the garments there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then he must bathe himself with water in a sacred place, put on his
        regular garments, and go out to sacrifice a burnt offering for himself and
        a burnt offering for the people. Through this process, he will purify himself
        and the people, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He must then burn all the fat of the sin offering on the altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe man chosen to drive the scapegoat into the wilderness of
        Azazel must wash his clothes and bathe himself in water. Then he may return
        to the camp.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThe bull and the goat presented as sin offerings, whose blood
        Aaron takes into the Most Holy Place for the purification ceremony, will
        be carried outside the camp. The animals\u2019 hides, internal organs, and
        dung are all to be burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The man who burns them must wash his clothes and bathe himself in
        water before returning to the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201COn the tenth day of the appointed month in early autumn,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        you must deny yourselves.[[COMMENT(1)]] Neither native-born Israelites nor
        foreigners living among you may do any kind of work. This is a permanent
        law for you. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:29a '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the tenth day of the seventh month. </b>This day in
          the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in September or October.
      - number: '16:29b '
        content: Or <b>must fast; </b>also in 16:31.
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "On that day offerings of purification will be made for you,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and you will be purified in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence
        from all your sins. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:30 '
        content: Or <b>atonement will be made for you, to purify you.</b>
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It will be a Sabbath day of complete rest for you, and you must deny
        yourselves. This is a permanent law for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In future generations, the purification[[COMMENT(0)]] ceremony will
        be performed by the priest who has been anointed and ordained to serve as
        high priest in place of his ancestor Aaron. He will put on the holy linen
        garments '
      comments:
      - number: '16:32 '
        content: Or <b>atonement.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and purify the Most Holy Place, the Tabernacle, the altar, the priests,
        and the entire congregation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "This is a permanent law for you, to purify the people of Israel from
        their sins, making them right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> once each
        year.\u201DMoses followed all these instructions exactly as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded him."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prohibitions against Eating Blood'
      title: Prohibitions against Eating Blood
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to Aaron and his sons and all
        the people of Israel. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has commanded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CIf any native Israelite sacrifices a bull[[COMMENT(0)]] or
        a lamb or a goat anywhere inside or outside the camp "
      comments:
      - number: '17:3 '
        content: Or <b>cow.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'instead of bringing it to the entrance of the Tabernacle[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to present it as an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that person
        will be as guilty as a murderer.[[COMMENT(1)]] Such a person has shed blood
        and will be cut off from the community. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:4a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting; </b>also in 17:5, 6, 9.
      - number: '17:4b '
        content: Hebrew <b>will be guilty of blood.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The purpose of this rule is to stop the Israelites from sacrificing
        animals in the open fields. It will ensure that they bring their sacrifices
        to the priest at the entrance of the Tabernacle, so he can present them to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as peace offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the priest will be able to splatter the blood against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        altar at the entrance of the Tabernacle, and he will burn the fat as a pleasing
        aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The people must no longer be unfaithful to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by offering sacrifices to the goat idols.[[COMMENT(0)]] This is a permanent
        law for them, to be observed from generation to generation.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:7 '
        content: Or <b>goat demons.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CGive them this command as well. If any native Israelite or
        foreigner living among you offers a burnt offering or a sacrifice "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but does not bring it to the entrance of the Tabernacle to offer
        it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that person will be cut off from the
        community.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd if any native Israelite or foreigner living among you eats
        or drinks blood in any form, I will turn against that person and cut him
        off from the community of your people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'for the life of the body is in its blood. I have given you the blood
        on the altar to purify you, making you right with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        It is the blood, given in exchange for a life, that makes purification possible. '
      comments:
      - number: '17:11 '
        content: Or <b>to make atonement for you.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "That is why I have said to the people of Israel, \u2018You must never
        eat or drink blood\u2014neither you nor the foreigners living among you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CAnd if any native Israelite or foreigner living among you goes
        hunting and kills an animal or bird that is approved for eating, he must
        drain its blood and cover it with earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The life of every creature is in its blood. That is why I have said
        to the people of Israel, \u2018You must never eat or drink blood, for the
        life of any creature is in its blood.\u2019 So whoever consumes blood will
        be cut off from the community.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd if any native-born Israelites or foreigners eat the meat
        of an animal that died naturally or was torn up by wild animals, they must
        wash their clothes and bathe themselves in water. They will remain ceremonially
        unclean until evening, but then they will be clean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But if they do not wash their clothes and bathe themselves, they
        will be punished for their sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Forbidden Sexual Practices'
      title: Forbidden Sexual Practices
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. I
        am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So do not act like the people in Egypt, where you used to live, or
        like the people of Canaan, where I am taking you. You must not imitate their
        way of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You must obey all my regulations and be careful to obey my decrees,
        for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If you obey my decrees and my regulations, you will find life through
        them. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou must never have sexual relations with a close relative,
        for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CDo not violate your father by having sexual relations with
        your mother. She is your mother; you must not have sexual relations with
        her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with any of your father\u2019s
        wives, for this would violate your father.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your sister or half sister,
        whether she is your father\u2019s daughter or your mother\u2019s daughter,
        whether she was born into your household or someone else\u2019s.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your granddaughter, whether
        she is your son\u2019s daughter or your daughter\u2019s daughter, for this
        would violate yourself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your stepsister, the daughter
        of any of your father\u2019s wives, for she is your sister.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your father\u2019s sister,
        for she is your father\u2019s close relative.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your mother\u2019s sister,
        for she is your mother\u2019s close relative.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDo not violate your uncle, your father\u2019s brother, by having
        sexual relations with his wife, for she is your aunt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your daughter-in-law; she
        is your son\u2019s wife, so you must not have sexual relations with her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your brother\u2019s wife,
        for this would violate your brother.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with both a woman and her daughter.
        And do not take[[COMMENT(0)]] her granddaughter, whether her son\u2019s daughter
        or her daughter\u2019s daughter, and have sexual relations with her. They
        are close relatives, and this would be a wicked act.  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:17 '
        content: Or <b>do not marry.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CWhile your wife is living, do not marry her sister and have
        sexual relations with her, for they would be rivals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with a woman during her period
        of menstrual impurity.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CDo not defile yourself by having sexual intercourse with your
        neighbor\u2019s wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CDo not permit any of your children to be offered as a sacrifice
        to Molech, for you must not bring shame on the name of your God. I am the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CDo not practice homosexuality, having sex with another man
        as with a woman. It is a detestable sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CA man must not defile himself by having sex with an animal.
        And a woman must not offer herself to a male animal to have intercourse with
        it. This is a perverse act.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CDo not defile yourselves in any of these ways, for the people
        I am driving out before you have defiled themselves in all these ways. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Because the entire land has become defiled, I am punishing the people
        who live there. I will cause the land to vomit them out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You must obey all my decrees and regulations. You must not commit
        any of these detestable sins. This applies both to native-born Israelites
        and to the foreigners living among you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CAll these detestable activities are practiced by the people
        of the land where I am taking you, and this is how the land has become defiled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So do not defile the land and give it a reason to vomit you out,
        as it will vomit out the people who live there now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Whoever commits any of these detestable sins will be cut off from
        the community of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So obey my instructions, and do not defile yourselves by committing
        any of these detestable practices that were committed by the people who lived
        in the land before you. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Holiness in Personal Conduct'
      title: Holiness in Personal Conduct
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the entire community of
        Israel. You must be holy because I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, am holy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CEach of you must show great respect for your mother and father,
        and you must always observe my Sabbath days of rest. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDo not put your trust in idols or make metal images of gods
        for yourselves. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhen you sacrifice a peace offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        offer it properly so you[[COMMENT(0)]] will be accepted by God. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:5 '
        content: Or <b>it.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sacrifice must be eaten on the same day you offer it or on the
        next day. Whatever is left over until the third day must be completely burned
        up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If any of the sacrifice is eaten on the third day, it will be contaminated,
        and I will not accept it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Anyone who eats it on the third day will be punished for defiling
        what is holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and will be cut off from
        the community.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen you harvest the crops of your land, do not harvest the
        grain along the edges of your fields, and do not pick up what the harvesters
        drop. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "It is the same with your grape crop\u2014do not strip every last
        bunch of grapes from the vines, and do not pick up the grapes that fall to
        the ground. Leave them for the poor and the foreigners living among you.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CDo not steal.\u201CDo not deceive or cheat one another.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CDo not bring shame on the name of your God by using it to swear
        falsely. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CDo not defraud or rob your neighbor.\u201CDo not make your
        hired workers wait until the next day to receive their pay.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDo not insult the deaf or cause the blind to stumble. You must
        fear your God; I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDo not twist justice in legal matters by favoring the poor
        or being partial to the rich and powerful. Always judge people fairly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDo not spread slanderous gossip among your people.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CDo
        not stand idly by when your neighbor\u2019s life is threatened. I am the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Do not act as a merchant toward your own people.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CDo not nurse hatred in your heart for any of your relatives.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Confront people directly so you will not be held guilty for their sin.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>for your brother.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CDo not seek revenge or bear a grudge against a fellow Israelite,
        but love your neighbor as yourself. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou must obey all my decrees.\u201CDo not mate two different
        kinds of animals. Do not plant your field with two different kinds of seed.
        Do not wear clothing woven from two different kinds of thread.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CIf a man has sex with a slave girl whose freedom has never
        been purchased but who is committed to become another man\u2019s wife, he
        must pay full compensation to her master. But since she is not a free woman,
        neither the man nor the woman will be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The man, however, must bring a ram as a guilt offering and present
        it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the entrance of the Tabernacle.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tent of Meeting.</b>
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The priest will then purify him[[COMMENT(0)]] before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with the ram of the guilt offering, and the man\u2019s sin will be forgiven.  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:22 '
        content: Or <b>make atonement for him.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CWhen you enter the land and plant fruit trees, leave the fruit
        unharvested for the first three years and consider it forbidden.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Do not eat it. "
      comments:
      - number: '19:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>consider it uncircumcised.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In the fourth year the entire crop must be consecrated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a celebration of praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Finally, in the fifth year you may eat the fruit. If you follow this
        pattern, your harvest will increase. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CDo not eat meat that has not been drained of its blood.\u201CDo
        not practice fortune-telling or witchcraft.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CDo not trim off the hair on your temples or trim your beards.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CDo not cut your bodies for the dead, and do not mark your skin
        with tattoos. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CDo not defile your daughter by making her a prostitute, or
        the land will be filled with prostitution and wickedness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CKeep my Sabbath days of rest, and show reverence toward my
        sanctuary. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CDo not defile yourselves by turning to mediums or to those
        who consult the spirits of the dead. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CStand up in the presence of the elderly, and show respect for
        the aged. Fear your God. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CDo not take advantage of foreigners who live among you in your
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Treat them like native-born Israelites, and love them as you love
        yourself. Remember that you were once foreigners living in the land of Egypt.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CDo not use dishonest standards when measuring length, weight,
        or volume. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Your scales and weights must be accurate. Your containers for measuring
        dry materials or liquids must be accurate.[[COMMENT(0)]] I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God who brought you out of the land of Egypt.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:36 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Use an honest ephah </b>[a dry measure] <b>and an honest
          hin </b>[a liquid measure].
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CYou must be careful to keep all of my decrees and regulations
        by putting them into practice. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Punishments for Disobedience'
      title: Punishments for Disobedience
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the people of Israel these instructions, which apply both
        to native Israelites and to the foreigners living in Israel.\u201CIf any
        of them offer their children as a sacrifice to Molech, they must be put to
        death. The people of the community must stone them to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I myself will turn against them and cut them off from the community,
        because they have defiled my sanctuary and brought shame on my holy name
        by offering their children to Molech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And if the people of the community ignore those who offer their children
        to Molech and refuse to execute them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I myself will turn against them and their families and will cut them
        off from the community. This will happen to all who commit spiritual prostitution
        by worshiping Molech.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI will also turn against those who commit spiritual prostitution
        by putting their trust in mediums or in those who consult the spirits of
        the dead. I will cut them off from the community. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So set yourselves apart to be holy, for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Keep all my decrees by putting them into practice, for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who makes you holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnyone who dishonors[[COMMENT(0)]] father or mother must be
        put to death. Such a person is guilty of a capital offense.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:9 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Anyone who speaks disrespectfully of. </b>Compare
          Matt 15:4; Mark 7:10.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf a man commits adultery with his neighbor\u2019s wife, both
        the man and the woman who have committed adultery must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CIf a man violates his father by having sex with one of his
        father\u2019s wives, both the man and the woman must be put to death, for
        they are guilty of a capital offense.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIf a man has sex with his daughter-in-law, both must be put
        to death. They have committed a perverse act and are guilty of a capital
        offense.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf a man practices homosexuality, having sex with another man
        as with a woman, both men have committed a detestable act. They must both
        be put to death, for they are guilty of a capital offense.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIf a man marries both a woman and her mother, he has committed
        a wicked act. The man and both women must be burned to death to wipe out
        such wickedness from among you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf a man has sex with an animal, he must be put to death, and
        the animal must be killed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf a woman presents herself to a male animal to have intercourse
        with it, she and the animal must both be put to death. You must kill both,
        for they are guilty of a capital offense.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CIf a man marries his sister, the daughter of either his father
        or his mother, and they have sexual relations, it is a shameful disgrace.
        They must be publicly cut off from the community. Since the man has violated
        his sister, he will be punished for his sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf a man has sexual relations with a woman during her menstrual
        period, both of them must be cut off from the community, for together they
        have exposed the source of her blood flow.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CDo not have sexual relations with your aunt, whether your mother\u2019s
        sister or your father\u2019s sister. This would dishonor a close relative.
        Both parties are guilty and will be punished for their sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CIf a man has sex with his uncle\u2019s wife, he has violated
        his uncle. Both the man and woman will be punished for their sin, and they
        will die childless.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIf a man marries his brother\u2019s wife, it is an act of impurity.
        He has violated his brother, and the guilty couple will remain childless.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYou must keep all my decrees and regulations by putting them
        into practice; otherwise the land to which I am bringing you as your new
        home will vomit you out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Do not live according to the customs of the people I am driving out
        before you. It is because they do these shameful things that I detest them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But I have promised you, \u2018You will possess their land because
        I will give it to you as your possession\u2014a land flowing with milk and
        honey.\u2019 I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who has set you
        apart from all other people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYou must therefore make a distinction between ceremonially
        clean and unclean animals, and between clean and unclean birds. You must
        not defile yourselves by eating any unclean animal or bird or creature that
        scurries along the ground. I have identified them as being unclean for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You must be holy because I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am holy.
        I have set you apart from all other people to be my very own.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CMen and women among you who act as mediums or who consult the
        spirits of the dead must be put to death by stoning. They are guilty of a
        capital offense.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Instructions for the Priests'
      title: Instructions for the Priests
      number: 1
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, \u201CGive the following
        instructions to the priests, the descendants of Aaron.\u201CA priest must
        not make himself ceremonially unclean by touching the dead body of a relative. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The only exceptions are his closest relatives\u2014his mother or
        father, son or daughter, brother, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'or his virgin sister who depends on him because she has no husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But a priest must not defile himself and make himself unclean for
        someone who is related to him only by marriage.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe priests must not shave their heads or trim their beards
        or cut their bodies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They must be set apart as holy to their God and must never bring
        shame on the name of God. They must be holy, for they are the ones who present
        the special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, gifts of food for their
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CPriests may not marry a woman defiled by prostitution, and
        they may not marry a woman who is divorced from her husband, for the priests
        are set apart as holy to their God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You must treat them as holy because they offer up food to your God.
        You must consider them holy because I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am
        holy, and I make you holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf a priest\u2019s daughter defiles herself by becoming a prostitute,
        she also defiles her father\u2019s holiness, and she must be burned to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe high priest has the highest rank of all the priests. The
        anointing oil has been poured on his head, and he has been ordained to wear
        the priestly garments. He must never leave his hair uncombed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        or tear his clothing. "
      comments:
      - number: '21:10 '
        content: Or <b>never uncover his head.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He must not defile himself by going near a dead body. He may not
        make himself ceremonially unclean even for his father or mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He must not defile the sanctuary of his God by leaving it to attend
        to a dead person, for he has been made holy by the anointing oil of his God.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThe high priest may marry only a virgin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He may not marry a widow, a woman who is divorced, or a woman who
        has defiled herself by prostitution. She must be a virgin from his own clan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "so that he will not dishonor his descendants among his clan, for
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who makes him holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to Aaron: In all future generations,
        none of your descendants who has any defect will qualify to offer food to
        his God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'No one who has a defect qualifies, whether he is blind, lame, disfigured,
        deformed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'or has a broken foot or arm, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'or is hunchbacked or dwarfed, or has a defective eye, or skin sores
        or scabs, or damaged testicles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'No descendant of Aaron who has a defect may approach the altar to
        present special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Since he has a
        defect, he may not approach the altar to offer food to his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'However, he may eat from the food offered to God, including the holy
        offerings and the most holy offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Yet because of his physical defect, he may not enter the room behind
        the inner curtain or approach the altar, for this would defile my holy places.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who makes them holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So Moses gave these instructions to Aaron and his sons and to all
        the Israelites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTell Aaron and his sons to be very careful with the sacred
        gifts that the Israelites set apart for me, so they do not bring shame on
        my holy name. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Give them the following instructions.\u201CIn all future generations,
        if any of your descendants is ceremonially unclean when he approaches the
        sacred offerings that the people of Israel consecrate to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        he must be cut off from my presence. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIf any of Aaron\u2019s descendants has a skin disease[[COMMENT(0)]]
        or any kind of discharge that makes him ceremonially unclean, he may not
        eat from the sacred offerings until he has been pronounced clean. He also
        becomes unclean by touching a corpse, or by having an emission of semen, "
      comments:
      - number: '22:4 '
        content: Traditionally rendered <b>leprosy; </b>see note on 13:2a.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'or by touching a small animal that is unclean, or by touching someone
        who is ceremonially unclean for any reason. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The man who is defiled in any of these ways will remain unclean until
        evening. He may not eat from the sacred offerings until he has bathed himself
        in water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the sun goes down, he will be ceremonially clean again and may
        eat from the sacred offerings, for this is his food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He may not eat an animal that has died a natural death or has been
        torn apart by wild animals, for this would defile him. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe priests must follow my instructions carefully. Otherwise
        they will be punished for their sin and will die for violating my instructions.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who makes them holy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNo one outside a priest\u2019s family may eat the sacred offerings.
        Even guests and hired workers in a priest\u2019s home are not allowed to
        eat them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'However, if the priest buys a slave for himself, the slave may eat
        from the sacred offerings. And if his slaves have children, they also may
        share his food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If a priest\u2019s daughter marries someone outside the priestly
        family, she may no longer eat the sacred offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if she becomes a widow or is divorced and has no children to
        support her, and she returns to live in her father\u2019s home as in her
        youth, she may eat her father\u2019s food again. Otherwise, no one outside
        a priest\u2019s family may eat the sacred offerings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAny such person who eats the sacred offerings without realizing
        it must pay the priest for the amount eaten, plus an additional 20 percent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The priests must not let the Israelites defile the sacred offerings
        brought to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Worthy and Unworthy Offerings'
      title: Worthy and Unworthy Offerings
      number: 16
      content: "by allowing unauthorized people to eat them. This would bring guilt
        upon them and require them to pay compensation. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        who makes them holy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CGive Aaron and his sons and all the Israelites these instructions,
        which apply both to native Israelites and to the foreigners living among
        you.\u201CIf you present a gift as a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        whether it is to fulfill a vow or is a voluntary offering, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'you[[COMMENT(0)]] will be accepted only if your offering is a male
        animal with no defects. It may be a bull, a ram, or a male goat. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:19 '
        content: Or <b>it.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not present an animal with defects, because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will not accept it on your behalf.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIf you present a peace offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from the herd or the flock, whether it is to fulfill a vow or is a voluntary
        offering, you must offer a perfect animal. It may have no defect of any kind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You must not offer an animal that is blind, crippled, or injured,
        or that has a wart, a skin sore, or scabs. Such animals must never be offered
        on the altar as special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If a bull[[COMMENT(0)]] or lamb has a leg that is too long or too
        short, it may be offered as a voluntary offering, but it may not be offered
        to fulfill a vow. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:23 '
        content: Or <b>cow.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If an animal has damaged testicles or is castrated, you may not offer
        it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. You must never do this in your own
        land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and you must not accept such an animal from foreigners and then offer
        it as a sacrifice to your God. Such animals will not be accepted on your
        behalf, for they are mutilated or defective.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CWhen a calf or lamb or goat is born, it must be left with its
        mother for seven days. From the eighth day on, it will be acceptable as a
        special gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But you must not slaughter a mother animal and her offspring on the
        same day, whether from the herd or the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When you bring a thanksgiving offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        sacrifice it properly so you will be accepted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Eat the entire sacrificial animal on the day it is presented. Do
        not leave any of it until the next morning. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou must faithfully keep all my commands by putting them into
        practice, for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Do not bring shame on my holy name, for I will display my holiness
        among the people of Israel. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who makes
        you holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "It was I who rescued you from the land of Egypt, that I might be
        your God. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Appointed Festivals'
      title: The Appointed Festivals
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. These
        are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s appointed festivals, which you
        are to proclaim as official days for holy assembly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou have six days each week for your ordinary work, but the
        seventh day is a Sabbath day of complete rest, an official day for holy assembly.
        It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Sabbath day, and it must be
        observed wherever you live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Passover and the Festival of Unleavened Bread'
      title: Passover and the Festival of Unleavened Bread
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIn addition to the Sabbath, these are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        appointed festivals, the official days for holy assembly that are to be celebrated
        at their proper times each year.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Passover begins at sundown
        on the fourteenth day of the first month.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:5 '
        content: This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in late March,
          April, or early May.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the next day, the fifteenth day of the month, you must begin celebrating
        the Festival of Unleavened Bread. This festival to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        continues for seven days, and during that time the bread you eat must be
        made without yeast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On the first day of the festival, all the people must stop their
        ordinary work and observe an official day for holy assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Celebration of First Harvest'
      title: Celebration of First Harvest
      number: 8
      content: "For seven days you must present special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        On the seventh day the people must again stop all their ordinary work to
        observe an official day for holy assembly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. When
        you enter the land I am giving you and you harvest its first crops, bring
        the priest a bundle of grain from the first cutting of your grain harvest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On the day after the Sabbath, the priest will lift it up before the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> so it may be accepted on your behalf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On that same day you must sacrifice a one-year-old male lamb with
        no defects as a burnt offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'With it you must present a grain offering consisting of four quarts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of choice flour moistened with olive oil. It will be a special gift, a pleasing
        aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. You must also offer one quart[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of wine as a liquid offering. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:13a '
        content: Hebrew <b>2/10 of an ephah </b>[4.4 liters]; also in 23:17.
      - number: '23:13b '
        content: Hebrew <b>1/4 of a hin </b>[1 liter].
    - name: '14: The Festival of Harvest'
      title: The Festival of Harvest
      number: 14
      content: 'Do not eat any bread or roasted grain or fresh kernels on that day
        until you bring this offering to your God. This is a permanent law for you,
        and it must be observed from generation to generation wherever you live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CFrom the day after the Sabbath\u2014the day you bring the bundle
        of grain to be lifted up as a special offering\u2014count off seven full
        weeks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Keep counting until the day after the seventh Sabbath, fifty days
        later. Then present an offering of new grain to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'From wherever you live, bring two loaves of bread to be lifted up
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as a special offering. Make these
        loaves from four quarts of choice flour, and bake them with yeast. They will
        be an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from the first of your
        crops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Along with the bread, present seven one-year-old male lambs with
        no defects, one young bull, and two rams as burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        These burnt offerings, together with the grain offerings and liquid offerings,
        will be a special gift, a pleasing aroma to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then you must offer one male goat as a sin offering and two one-year-old
        male lambs as a peace offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe priest will lift up the two lambs as a special offering
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, together with the loaves representing
        the first of your crops. These offerings, which are holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        belong to the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'That same day will be proclaimed an official day for holy assembly,
        a day on which you do no ordinary work. This is a permanent law for you,
        and it must be observed from generation to generation wherever you live.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:21 '
        content: This celebration, called the Festival of Harvest or the Festival
          of Weeks, was later called the Festival of Pentecost (see Acts 2:1). It
          is celebrated today as Shavuot (or Shabuoth).
    - name: '22: The Festival of Trumpets'
      title: The Festival of Trumpets
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CWhen you harvest the crops of your land, do not harvest the
        grain along the edges of your fields, and do not pick up what the harvesters
        drop. Leave it for the poor and the foreigners living among you. I am the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. On
        the first day of the appointed month in early autumn,[[COMMENT(0)]] you are
        to observe a day of complete rest. It will be an official day for holy assembly,
        a day commemorated with loud blasts of a trumpet. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the first day of the seventh month. </b>This day in
          the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred in September or October. This
          festival is celebrated today as Rosh Hashanah, the Jewish new year.
    - name: '25: The Day of Atonement'
      title: The Day of Atonement
      number: 25
      content: "You must do no ordinary work on that day. Instead, you are to present
        special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBe careful to celebrate the Day of Atonement on the tenth day
        of that same month\u2014nine days after the Festival of Trumpets.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        You must observe it as an official day for holy assembly, a day to deny yourselves[[COMMENT(1)]]
        and present special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:27a '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the tenth day of the seventh month; </b>see 23:24 and
          the note there. This day in the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar occurred
          in September or October. It is celebrated today as Yom Kippur.
      - number: '23:27b '
        content: Or <b>to fast; </b>similarly in 23:29, 32.
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Do no work during that entire day because it is the Day of Atonement,
        when offerings of purification are made for you, making you right with[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:28 '
        content: Or <b>when atonement is made for you before.</b>
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "All who do not deny themselves that day will be cut off from God\u2019s
        people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And I will destroy anyone among you who does any work on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'You must not do any work at all! This is a permanent law for you,
        and it must be observed from generation to generation wherever you live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: The Festival of Shelters'
      title: The Festival of Shelters
      number: 32
      content: "This will be a Sabbath day of complete rest for you, and on that
        day you must deny yourselves. This day of rest will begin at sundown on the
        ninth day of the month and extend until sundown on the tenth day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. Begin
        celebrating the Festival of Shelters[[COMMENT(0)]] on the fifteenth day of
        the appointed month\u2014five days after the Day of Atonement.[[COMMENT(1)]]
        This festival to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will last for seven days. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:34a '
        content: Or <b>Festival of Booths, </b>or <b>Festival of Tabernacles. </b>This
          was earlier called the Festival of the Final Harvest or Festival of Ingathering
          (see Exod 23:16b). It is celebrated today as Sukkot (or Succoth).
      - number: '23:34b '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the fifteenth day of the seventh month; </b>see 23:27a
          and the note there.
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'On the first day of the festival you must proclaim an official day
        for holy assembly, when you do no ordinary work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For seven days you must present special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        The eighth day is another holy day on which you present your special gifts
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. This will be a solemn occasion, and no
        ordinary work may be done that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "(\u201CThese are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s appointed
        festivals. Celebrate them each year as official days for holy assembly by
        presenting special gifts to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014burnt offerings,
        grain offerings, sacrifices, and liquid offerings\u2014each on its proper
        day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "These festivals must be observed in addition to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        regular Sabbath days, and the offerings are in addition to your personal
        gifts, the offerings you give to fulfill your vows, and the voluntary offerings
        you present to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.)  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CRemember that this seven-day festival to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014the
        Festival of Shelters\u2014begins on the fifteenth day of the appointed month,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        after you have harvested all the produce of the land. The first day and the
        eighth day of the festival will be days of complete rest. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:39 '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the fifteenth day of the seventh month.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "On the first day gather branches from magnificent trees[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014palm
        fronds, boughs from leafy trees, and willows that grow by the streams. Then
        celebrate with joy before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God for seven
        days. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:40 '
        content: Or <b>gather fruit from majestic trees.</b>
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You must observe this festival to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for seven days every year. This is a permanent law for you, and it must be
        observed in the appointed month[[COMMENT(0)]] from generation to generation. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:41 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the seventh month.</b>
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'For seven days you must live outside in little shelters. All native-born
        Israelites must live in shelters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "This will remind each new generation of Israelites that I made their
        ancestors live in shelters when I rescued them from the land of Egypt. I
        am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: So Moses gave the Israelites these instructions regarding the annual
        festivals of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pure Oil and Holy Bread'
      title: Pure Oil and Holy Bread
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CCommand the people of Israel to bring you pure oil of pressed
        olives for the light, to keep the lamps burning continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "This is the lampstand that stands in the Tabernacle, in front of
        the inner curtain that shields the Ark of the Covenant.[[COMMENT(0)]] Aaron
        must keep the lamps burning in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence
        all night. This is a permanent law for you, and it must be observed from
        generation to generation. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in the Tent of Meeting, outside the inner curtain of the
          Testimony; </b>see note on 16:13.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Aaron and the priests must tend the lamps on the pure gold lampstand
        continually in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CYou must bake twelve flat loaves of bread from choice flour,
        using four quarts[[COMMENT(0)]] of flour for each loaf. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>2/10 of an ephah </b>[4.4 liters].
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Place the bread before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the pure
        gold table, and arrange the loaves in two stacks, with six loaves in each
        stack. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Put some pure frankincense near each stack to serve as a representative
        offering, a special gift presented to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Every Sabbath day this bread must be laid out before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as a gift from the Israelites; it is an ongoing expression of the eternal
        covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: An Example of Just Punishment'
      title: An Example of Just Punishment
      number: 9
      content: "The loaves of bread will belong to Aaron and his descendants, who
        must eat them in a sacred place, for they are most holy. It is the permanent
        right of the priests to claim this portion of the special gifts presented
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One day a man who had an Israelite mother and an Egyptian father
        came out of his tent and got into a fight with one of the Israelite men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'During the fight, this son of an Israelite woman blasphemed the Name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]] with a curse. So the man
        was brought to Moses for judgment. His mother was Shelomith, the daughter
        of Dibri of the tribe of Dan. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Name; </b>also in 24:16b.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They kept the man in custody until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        will in the matter should become clear to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTake the blasphemer outside the camp, and tell all those who
        heard the curse to lay their hands on his head. Then let the entire community
        stone him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Say to the people of Israel: Those who curse their God will be punished
        for their sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Anyone who blasphemes the Name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        must be stoned to death by the whole community of Israel. Any native-born
        Israelite or foreigner among you who blasphemes the Name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        must be put to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnyone who takes another person\u2019s life must be put to
        death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnyone who kills another person\u2019s animal must pay for
        it in full\u2014a live animal for the animal that was killed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAnyone who injures another person must be dealt with according
        to the injury inflicted\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'a fracture for a fracture, an eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.
        Whatever anyone does to injure another person must be paid back in kind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWhoever kills an animal must pay for it in full, but whoever
        kills another person must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThis same standard applies both to native-born Israelites and
        to the foreigners living among you. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: After Moses gave all these instructions to the Israelites, they took
        the blasphemer outside the camp and stoned him to death. The Israelites did
        just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sabbath Year'
      title: The Sabbath Year
      number: 1
      content: '  While Moses was on Mount Sinai, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. When
        you have entered the land I am giving you, the land itself must observe a
        Sabbath rest before the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>every seventh year. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For six years you may plant your fields and prune your vineyards
        and harvest your crops, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but during the seventh year the land must have a Sabbath year of
        complete rest. It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Sabbath. Do not
        plant your fields or prune your vineyards during that year. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And don\u2019t store away the crops that grow on their own or gather
        the grapes from your unpruned vines. The land must have a year of complete
        rest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you may eat whatever the land produces on its own during its
        Sabbath. This applies to you, your male and female servants, your hired workers,
        and the temporary residents who live with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Year of Jubilee'
      title: The Year of Jubilee
      number: 7
      content: 'Your livestock and the wild animals in your land will also be allowed
        to eat what the land produces.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIn addition, you must count off seven Sabbath years, seven
        sets of seven years, adding up to forty-nine years in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then on the Day of Atonement in the fiftieth year,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        blow the ram\u2019s horn loud and long throughout the land. "
      comments:
      - number: '25:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the tenth day of the seventh month, on the Day of Atonement;
          </b>see 23:27a and the note there.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Set this year apart as holy, a time to proclaim freedom throughout
        the land for all who live there. It will be a jubilee year for you, when
        each of you may return to the land that belonged to your ancestors and return
        to your own clan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This fiftieth year will be a jubilee for you. During that year you
        must not plant your fields or store away any of the crops that grow on their
        own, and don\u2019t gather the grapes from your unpruned vines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It will be a jubilee year for you, and you must keep it holy. But
        you may eat whatever the land produces on its own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In the Year of Jubilee each of you may return to the land that belonged
        to your ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhen you make an agreement with your neighbor to buy or sell
        property, you must not take advantage of each other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When you buy land from your neighbor, the price you pay must be based
        on the number of years since the last jubilee. The seller must set the price
        by taking into account the number of years remaining until the next Year
        of Jubilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The more years until the next jubilee, the higher the price; the
        fewer years, the lower the price. After all, the person selling the land
        is actually selling you a certain number of harvests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Show your fear of God by not taking advantage of each other. I am
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf you want to live securely in the land, follow my decrees
        and obey my regulations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the land will yield large crops, and you will eat your fill
        and live securely in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But you might ask, \u2018What will we eat during the seventh year,
        since we are not allowed to plant or harvest crops that year?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Be assured that I will send my blessing for you in the sixth year,
        so the land will produce a crop large enough for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Redemption of Property'
      title: Redemption of Property
      number: 22
      content: 'When you plant your fields in the eighth year, you will still be
        eating from the large crop of the sixth year. In fact, you will still be
        eating from that large crop when the new crop is harvested in the ninth year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CThe land must never be sold on a permanent basis, for the land
        belongs to me. You are only foreigners and tenant farmers working for me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CWith every purchase of land you must grant the seller the right
        to buy it back. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'If one of your fellow Israelites falls into poverty and is forced
        to sell some family land, then a close relative should buy it back for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'If there is no close relative to buy the land, but the person who
        sold it gets enough money to buy it back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'he then has the right to redeem it from the one who bought it. The
        price of the land will be discounted according to the number of years until
        the next Year of Jubilee. In this way the original owner can then return
        to the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But if the original owner cannot afford to buy back the land, it
        will remain with the new owner until the next Year of Jubilee. In the jubilee
        year, the land must be returned to the original owners so they can return
        to their family land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CAnyone who sells a house inside a walled town has the right
        to buy it back for a full year after its sale. During that year, the seller
        retains the right to buy it back. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But if it is not bought back within a year, the sale of the house
        within the walled town cannot be reversed. It will become the permanent property
        of the buyer. It will not be returned to the original owner in the Year of
        Jubilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But a house in a village\u2014a settlement without fortified walls\u2014will
        be treated like property in the countryside. Such a house may be bought back
        at any time, and it must be returned to the original owner in the Year of
        Jubilee.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CThe Levites always have the right to buy back a house they
        have sold within the towns allotted to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And any property that is sold by the Levites\u2014all houses within
        the Levitical towns\u2014must be returned in the Year of Jubilee. After all,
        the houses in the towns reserved for the Levites are the only property they
        own in all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Redemption of the Poor and Enslaved'
      title: Redemption of the Poor and Enslaved
      number: 34
      content: 'The open pastureland around the Levitical towns may never be sold.
        It is their permanent possession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CIf one of your fellow Israelites falls into poverty and cannot
        support himself, support him as you would a foreigner or a temporary resident
        and allow him to live with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Do not charge interest or make a profit at his expense. Instead,
        show your fear of God by letting him live with you as your relative. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Remember, do not charge interest on money you lend him or make a
        profit on food you sell him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who brought you out
        of the land of Egypt to give you the land of Canaan and to be your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CIf one of your fellow Israelites falls into poverty and is
        forced to sell himself to you, do not treat him as a slave. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Treat him instead as a hired worker or as a temporary resident who
        lives with you, and he will serve you only until the Year of Jubilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'At that time he and his children will no longer be obligated to you,
        and they will return to their clans and go back to the land originally allotted
        to their ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The people of Israel are my servants, whom I brought out of the land
        of Egypt, so they must never be sold as slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Show your fear of God by not treating them harshly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CHowever, you may purchase male and female slaves from among
        the nations around you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'You may also purchase the children of temporary residents who live
        among you, including those who have been born in your land. You may treat
        them as your property, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'passing them on to your children as a permanent inheritance. You
        may treat them as slaves, but you must never treat your fellow Israelites
        this way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CSuppose a foreigner or temporary resident becomes rich while
        living among you. If any of your fellow Israelites fall into poverty and
        are forced to sell themselves to such a foreigner or to a member of his family, "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'they still retain the right to be bought back, even after they have
        been purchased. They may be bought back by a brother, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'an uncle, or a cousin. In fact, anyone from the extended family may
        buy them back. They may also redeem themselves if they have prospered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "They will negotiate the price of their freedom with the person who
        bought them. The price will be based on the number of years from the time
        they were sold until the next Year of Jubilee\u2014whatever it would cost
        to hire a worker for that period of time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'If many years still remain until the jubilee, they will repay the
        proper proportion of what they received when they sold themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'If only a few years remain until the Year of Jubilee, they will repay
        a small amount for their redemption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'The foreigner must treat them as workers hired on a yearly basis.
        You must not allow a foreigner to treat any of your fellow Israelites harshly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'If any Israelites have not been bought back by the time the Year
        of Jubilee arrives, they and their children must be set free at that time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: For the people of Israel belong to me. They are my servants, whom
        I brought out of the land of Egypt. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Blessings for Obedience'
      title: Blessings for Obedience
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CDo not make idols or set up carved images, or sacred pillars,
        or sculptured stones in your land so you may worship them. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You must keep my Sabbath days of rest and show reverence for my sanctuary.
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CIf you follow my decrees and are careful to obey my commands, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will send you the seasonal rains. The land will then yield its
        crops, and the trees of the field will produce their fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your threshing season will overlap with the grape harvest, and your
        grape harvest will overlap with the season of planting grain. You will eat
        your fill and live securely in your own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI will give you peace in the land, and you will be able to
        sleep with no cause for fear. I will rid the land of wild animals and keep
        your enemies out of your land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In fact, you will chase down your enemies and slaughter them with
        your swords. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Five of you will chase a hundred, and a hundred of you will chase
        ten thousand! All your enemies will fall beneath your sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI will look favorably upon you, making you fertile and multiplying
        your people. And I will fulfill my covenant with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You will have such a surplus of crops that you will need to clear
        out the old grain to make room for the new harvest! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will live among you, and I will not despise you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will walk among you; I will be your God, and you will be my people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Punishments for Disobedience'
      title: Punishments for Disobedience
      number: 13
      content: 'I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who brought you out
        of the land of Egypt so you would no longer be their slaves. I broke the
        yoke of slavery from your neck so you can walk with your heads held high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHowever, if you do not listen to me or obey all these commands, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and if you break my covenant by rejecting my decrees, treating my
        regulations with contempt, and refusing to obey my commands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will punish you. I will bring sudden terrors upon you\u2014wasting
        diseases and burning fevers that will cause your eyes to fail and your life
        to ebb away. You will plant your crops in vain because your enemies will
        eat them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I will turn against you, and you will be defeated by your enemies.
        Those who hate you will rule over you, and you will run even when no one
        is chasing you!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd if, in spite of all this, you still disobey me, I will
        punish you seven times over for your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will break your proud spirit by making the skies as unyielding
        as iron and the earth as hard as bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'All your work will be for nothing, for your land will yield no crops,
        and your trees will bear no fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIf even then you remain hostile toward me and refuse to obey
        me, I will inflict disaster on you seven times over for your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I will send wild animals that will rob you of your children and destroy
        your livestock. Your numbers will dwindle, and your roads will be deserted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd if you fail to learn the lesson and continue your hostility
        toward me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'then I myself will be hostile toward you. I will personally strike
        you with calamity seven times over for your sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I will send armies against you to carry out the curse of the covenant
        you have broken. When you run to your towns for safety, I will send a plague
        to destroy you there, and you will be handed over to your enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will destroy your food supply, so that ten women will need only
        one oven to bake bread for their families. They will ration your food by
        weight, and though you have food to eat, you will not be satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CIf in spite of all this you still refuse to listen and still
        remain hostile toward me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'then I will give full vent to my hostility. I myself will punish
        you seven times over for your sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then you will eat the flesh of your own sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will destroy your pagan shrines and knock down your places of worship.
        I will leave your lifeless corpses piled on top of your lifeless idols,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and I will despise you. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:30 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung.
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'I will make your cities desolate and destroy your places of pagan
        worship. I will take no pleasure in your offerings that should be a pleasing
        aroma to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yes, I myself will devastate your land, and your enemies who come
        to occupy it will be appalled at what they see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'I will scatter you among the nations and bring out my sword against
        you. Your land will become desolate, and your cities will lie in ruins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then at last the land will enjoy its neglected Sabbath years as it
        lies desolate while you are in exile in the land of your enemies. Then the
        land will finally rest and enjoy the Sabbaths it missed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'As long as the land lies in ruins, it will enjoy the rest you never
        allowed it to take every seventh year while you lived in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CAnd for those of you who survive, I will demoralize you in
        the land of your enemies. You will live in such fear that the sound of a
        leaf driven by the wind will send you fleeing. You will run as though fleeing
        from a sword, and you will fall even when no one pursues you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Though no one is chasing you, you will stumble over each other as
        though fleeing from a sword. You will have no power to stand up against your
        enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'You will die among the foreign nations and be devoured in the land
        of your enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Those of you who survive will waste away in your enemies\u2019 lands
        because of their sins and the sins of their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CBut at last my people will confess their sins and the sins
        of their ancestors for betraying me and being hostile toward me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'When I have turned their hostility back on them and brought them
        to the land of their enemies, then at last their stubborn hearts will be
        humbled, and they will pay for their sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then I will remember my covenant with Jacob and my covenant with
        Isaac and my covenant with Abraham, and I will remember the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'For the land must be abandoned to enjoy its years of Sabbath rest
        as it lies deserted. At last the people will pay for their sins, for they
        have continually rejected my regulations and despised my decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CBut despite all this, I will not utterly reject or despise
        them while they are in exile in the land of their enemies. I will not cancel
        my covenant with them by wiping them out, for I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "For their sakes I will remember my ancient covenant with their ancestors,
        whom I brought out of the land of Egypt in the sight of all the nations,
        that I might be their God. I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: These are the decrees, regulations, and instructions that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave through Moses on Mount Sinai as evidence of the relationship between
        himself and the Israelites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Redemption of Gifts Offered to the '
      title: 'Redemption of Gifts Offered to the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said
        to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGive the following instructions to the people of Israel. If
        anyone makes a special vow to dedicate someone to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by paying the value of that person, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'here is the scale of values to be used. A man between the ages of
        twenty and sixty is valued at fifty shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver, as measured
        by the sanctuary shekel. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:3 '
        content: Or <b>20 ounces </b>[570 grams].
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A woman of that age is valued at thirty shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        silver. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:4 '
        content: Or <b>12 ounces </b>[342 grams].
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A boy between the ages of five and twenty is valued at twenty shekels
        of silver; a girl of that age is valued at ten shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:5 '
        content: Or <b>A boy . . . 8 ounces </b>[228 grams] <b>of silver; a girl
          . . . 4 ounces </b>[114 grams].
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A boy between the ages of one month and five years is valued at five
        shekels of silver; a girl of that age is valued at three shekels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:6 '
        content: Or <b>A boy . . . 2 ounces </b>[57 grams] <b>of silver; a girl .
          . . 1.2 ounces </b>[34 grams].
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A man older than sixty is valued at fifteen shekels of silver; a
        woman of that age is valued at ten shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:7 '
        content: Or <b>A man . . . 6 ounces </b>[171 grams] <b>of silver; a woman
          . . . 4 ounces </b>[114 grams].
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If you desire to make such a vow but cannot afford to pay the required
        amount, take the person to the priest. He will determine the amount for you
        to pay based on what you can afford.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIf your vow involves giving an animal that is acceptable as
        an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, any gift to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be considered holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You may not exchange or substitute it for another animal\u2014neither
        a good animal for a bad one nor a bad animal for a good one. But if you do
        exchange one animal for another, then both the original animal and its substitute
        will be considered holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If your vow involves an unclean animal\u2014one that is not acceptable
        as an offering to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014then you must bring
        the animal to the priest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He will assess its value, and his assessment will be final, whether
        high or low. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If you want to buy back the animal, you must pay the value set by
        the priest, plus 20 percent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIf someone dedicates a house to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the priest will come to assess its value. The priest\u2019s assessment will
        be final, whether high or low. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If the person who dedicated the house wants to buy it back, he must
        pay the value set by the priest, plus 20 percent. Then the house will again
        be his.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf someone dedicates to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> a piece
        of his family property, its value will be assessed according to the amount
        of seed required to plant it\u2014fifty shekels of silver for a field planted
        with five bushels of barley seed.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>50 shekels </b>[20 ounces or 570 grams] <b>of silver for
          a homer </b>[220 liters] <b>of barley seed.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If the field is dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the
        Year of Jubilee, then the entire assessment will apply. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if the field is dedicated after the Year of Jubilee, the priest
        will assess the land\u2019s value in proportion to the number of years left
        until the next Year of Jubilee. Its assessed value is reduced each year. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If the person who dedicated the field wants to buy it back, he must
        pay the value set by the priest, plus 20 percent. Then the field will again
        be legally his. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But if he does not want to buy it back, and it is sold to someone
        else, the field can no longer be bought back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When the field is released in the Year of Jubilee, it will be holy,
        a field specially set apart[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> for the </smallcaps><smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        It will become the property of the priests.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:21 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering; also in 27:28,
          29.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf someone dedicates to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> a field
        he has purchased but which is not part of his family property, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the priest will assess its value based on the number of years left
        until the next Year of Jubilee. On that day he must give the assessed value
        of the land as a sacred donation to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In the Year of Jubilee the field must be returned to the person from
        whom he purchased it, the one who inherited it as family property. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '(All the payments must be measured by the weight of the sanctuary
        shekel,[[COMMENT(0)]] which equals twenty gerahs.)  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:25 '
        content: Each shekel was about 0.4 ounces [11 grams] in weight.
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYou may not dedicate a firstborn animal to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for the firstborn of your cattle, sheep, and goats already belong to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "However, you may buy back the firstborn of a ceremonially unclean
        animal by paying the priest\u2019s assessment of its worth, plus 20 percent.
        If you do not buy it back, the priest will sell it at its assessed value.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CHowever, anything specially set apart for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014whether
        a person, an animal, or family property\u2014must never be sold or bought
        back. Anything devoted in this way has been set apart as holy, and it belongs
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'No person specially set apart for destruction may be bought back.
        Such a person must be put to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201COne-tenth of the produce of the land, whether grain from the
        fields or fruit from the trees, belongs to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and must be set apart to him as holy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "If you want to buy back the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s tenth
        of the grain or fruit, you must pay its value, plus 20 percent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Count off every tenth animal from your herds and flocks and set them
        apart for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "You may not pick and choose between good and bad animals, and you
        may not substitute one for another. But if you do exchange one animal for
        another, then both the original animal and its substitute will be considered
        holy and cannot be bought back.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: These are the commands that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave through
        Moses on Mount Sinai for the Israelites.
      comments: []
